title: marinated chicken
directions: Put chicken in a bowl and cover with Dale's seasoning; let stand for 30 minutes.
Bake or grill until done.
Delicious, no other spices are needed.

title: lemon squares
directions: Blend butter, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican meat loaf roll
directions: Combine meat, oats, eggs, Worcestershire sauce and pepper; mix well.
On waxed paper, press meat mixture into 20 x 10 1/2-inch rectangle.
Combine cream cheese and chilies; mix well.
Spread cream cheese mixture over meat mixture to within 1-inch of outer edge.
Roll jelly roll fashion, starting at narrow end.
Place in 12
x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with salsa; continue baking 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook mushrooms, garlic and onion in 2 tablespoons water for 2 to 3 minutes.
In small bowl, mix Ricotta cheese, carrot, spinach and egg whites.
Place 1/2 noodles in 12 x 8-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 sauce, 1/2 mushroom mixture and 1/2 Ricotta mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8.
Per Serving:
Calories: 180.
Fat:

title: potato salad
directions: Let potatoes cool.
Peel, dice or cut potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: grandma's crumb dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and place in baking dish.
Combine the next 4 ingredients and pour on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients, except half of the grated cheese and tortillas.
Spoon 1/2 of sour cream mixture into tortillas and roll, placing in casserole side by side.
Top the tortillas with remaining sour cream, the remaining half of grated cheese and second can of olives.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pot roasted wild duck
directions: Season the body cavity well and then put into the cavity the skinned onion whole, the piece of celery, the piece of bacon and the piece of apple.
Season the outer skin of the duck.
Select a heavy pot, such as cast-iron pot, deep enough to cover the duck and one which has a tight fitting lid.
Put enough oil into the pot to cover the bottom.
Put the whole duck into the cold oil.
Add 1 1/4 cups water.
Cover and place over medium heat on top of stove and cook until tender; should take from 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Pierce with fork to test for doneness.
When tender enough, permit the duck to brown slowly.
When sufficiently browned, add another cup of water. Cover and cook slowly a few minutes longer.
Serve gravy over rice.

title: original banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat bananas, sugar, oil, and egg.
In a medium bowl, combine both flours, baking soda and powder, and salt.
Add to banana mixture, stirring just until moist.
Stir in nuts or raisins.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to cool completely.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, squash, oil and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into floured loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until thick and smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until blended well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: apple cake(old family recipe)
directions: Mix together the oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Sift together the baking soda, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add the apples, raisins (optional) and the walnuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or more.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together using mixer or blender.
Spinach does not have to be cooked.
Recipe may be divided into half. Serve with raw vegetables or corn chips.

title: clams steamed in sherry
directions: Bring sherry and enough water to cover clams to boiling.
Add clams and be sure that there is enough liquid to cover them.
Add onion and pepper.
Cover and steam clams until clams open up.

title: one-pot noodle stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in larger skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Stir in noodles gradually.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes or until noodles are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream.
Do not boil.
Spoon into serving dish and garnish with parsley.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand except butterscotch chips. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put butterscotch chips over batter.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: celery and chestnut casserole
directions: Boil celery 8 minutes and drain.
Mix celery, chestnuts, pimento and undiluted soup.
Pour in buttered casserole.
Toss crumbs and margarine over top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: california blend vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Melt margarine and add remaining ingredients.
Cook the sauce until smooth, fold in vegetables. Cook 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with bread crumbs or onion rings or flakes.
Very Good!

title: fun sticks
directions: Toast bread slices under broiler on 1 side.
Butter other side and sprinkle onion or garlic salt, Parmesan cheese and oregano evenly over slices.
Remove crusts and cut into 1/2 -inch strips. Toast the buttered side until side is lightly browned.
Makes 4 sticks per slice.

title: company baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, for 3 hours at 350°, stirring occasionally.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and mayonnaise; add to fruit mix.

title: crock-pot veal scallopine
directions: Roll
veal
cubes
in seasoned flour and fry in hot oil until browned.
Put into crock-pot.
Add all remaining ingredients. Stir
well.
Cover
and cook on high for 1 hour, then on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve over rice or fettucini.

title: german chocolate cheese cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, eggs and sugar until smooth.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour in half of the cake mix. Spread on the cream cheese mix and top with the remaining cake batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Allow cake to cool and top with coconut-pecan frosting.

title: granny kelly's tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten eggs, then milk, vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together; take small amount out and place on cloth covered with flour.
Roll out with rolling pin, using flour to keep it from sticking.
Use cookie cutters to cut out and bake in 350° oven until golden brown. Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: leona's creamed peas
directions: Cook broth and peas in 2-quart pan.
Bring to boil for 2 minutes.
Pan-fry onions in butter.
Add flour and whipping cream and pimientos.
Add to chicken broth and peas.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook on medium heat for about 3 minutes.

title: raspberry sponge
directions: Mix gelatin and cold water.
Then add boiling water.

title: holiday coffee cake
directions: Combine scalded milk, salt, sugar and shortening.
Mix yeast with half the flour.
Add lukewarm scalded milk mixture.
Beat well.
Let rise until very light.
Add egg and remaining flour. Mix well.
Let rise.
Roll dough into a rectangle on lightly floured board.
Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon.
Brush with melted butter; spread with cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Form into a ring on greased baking sheet.
Pinch ends together to fasten.
Using large scissors, cut ring around edge at 2-inch intervals, leaving inner edge in tact.
Turn each to lie flat on the pan.
Let rise.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix taco mix and beans; spread in dish.
Spread sour cream over first mixture; add cheese, onion, olives and tomatoes on top. Refrigerate and serve with corn chips.

title: japanese breaded pork cutlets (tonkatsu)
directions: Crack eggs into bowl and stir until even consistency.
Pour bread crumbs onto a flat plate.
Pat dry pork chops with paper towel.
Dredge pork chop through flour to cover one side and turn over to cover the other side.
Apply medium downward pressure to the pork chops to improve adherence of the bread crumbs on the down side.
Flip pork chop once more in the bread crumbs and apply pressure again.
If the pork chop is thick, stand it on each edge in the bread crumbs to cover the sides as well as possible.
Heat oil in deep frying pan to 350° to 360°.
Place pork chops into the hot oil.
Turn after 2 to 3 minutes.
Continue frying until the outside is uniformly medium brown.
Total cooking time will be about 4 to 5 minutes.
Slice cooked pork chops into 1/2-inch thick strips and serve hot with tonkatsu sauce for dipping.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops and place in baking dish.
Place a tablespoon of raw rice, a slice of onion, a tablespoon of tomato and a piece of green pepper on each pork chop.
Mix salt, pepper and sugar together; sprinkle over chop mixture.
Cover with 2 cups of tomato juice.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cover with foil or lid.

title: noodles melba(low-fat)
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet while boiling noodles.
Wash hamburger by placing in colander under hot tap water after browning meat.
Return to skillet.
Add spaghetti sauce and heat.

title: quick buttermilk biscuits
directions: Slice butter into large bowl over the flour.
Cut into small pieces.
Add buttermilk and blend well.
Knead dough.
Cut out biscuits and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° until done. Yields about 24 biscuits.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease inside of 9 1/2-inch souffl dish.
In medium pan, heat butter till melted.
Add flour, salt, dry mustard and cayenne pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Heat until boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute. Stir in cheese till melted, remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemony in color.
Stir into cheese mixture.
Beat egg whites and creme of tarter into stiff peaks.
Stir 1/3 of egg whites into cheese mixture, carefully fold cheese mixture into egg whites.

title: no-bake granola breakfast bars
directions: Heat peanut butter and honey in a saucepan over low heat until creamy. Remove from heat and pour into a bowl to cool. Add granola, cereal, raisins and crushed graham crackers to the peanut butter mixture and stir well. Roll into tablespoon-sized balls and set on wax paper. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving. Try using your favorite ingredients. Makes approximately 32 cookies.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Dough should be quite stiff.
Bake in hot oven until set.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind all together except mayonnaise and cornstarch.
Drain off juice.
Mix and cook 20 minutes.
You have to stir often or it will stick.
Take the cornstarch and mix in a little water.
Add to the mixture.
Take off the stove; add the mayonnaise.
Stir to mix. Put in hot jars and seal.
Makes 10 pints.

title: chicken primavera
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; add chicken.
Cook and stir until browned.
Add broccoli, peas, carrot and onion.
Cook and stir until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in broth, basil and pepper.
Bring to boil. Stir in rice.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar, water and syrup to soft ball stage (240°).
Add peanuts and stir until light brown to 300°.
Remove from fire and add salt, soda and butter.
Stir until mixed thoroughly and pour on buttered cookie sheet.

title: irish bran bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all dry ingredients in a bowl. Make a circular hole in the middle and add buttermilk while mixing it with the flour in a circular motion.
Continue doing this until all is formed into a cake of dough.
Remove from the bowl.
Shake some flour on the counter and knead a little with hands.
Then form into a circle or round ball and flatten out a little.
Cut into four quarters and place on a floured pan.
When oven has reached 400°, put bread in it and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool.
Then enjoy a delicious slice of Irish Bran Bread coated with butter!

title: vegetable soup
directions: In 4-quart pan, melt margarine over medium heat. Dip stew meat in mixture of flour, salt and pepper and place in pan to brown about 10 minutes. Add tomato juice to pan along with potatoes (diced) and cabbage. Add finely chopped onion and mixed vegetables. Cook over medium heat for about 45 minutes to insure all vegetables are done.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, eggs, baking powder and flour.
Mix well, then add vanilla and almond.
Spread in greased 9-inch ring pan.
Put foil under pan so it does not leak.
Place on top of batter apples or blueberries, plums and peaches.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake plums at 400° for 40 minutes and other at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: sunday night supper
directions: Fry green pepper and onion in butter for a few minutes.
Add hamburger and condensed tomato soup.
Drain and add red kidney beans, saving the juice.
Season with salt, paprika, Worcestershire sauce and sage.
Simmer about 25 minutes, moistening with the bean liquid if needed.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done, then pull off into pieces. Cook broccoli 10 minutes and drain thoroughly. In separate bowl, combine soup, cheeses and mayonnaise and blend entirely. Spray casserole dish with Pam cooking spray. Cover the bottom of dish with a layer of chicken pieces. Spread the drained broccoli over chicken. Add soup mixture to cover broccoli and chicken. Sprinkle bread crumbs and spray with Pam butter spray to add color and flavor before baking. Bake casserole at 350° for 35 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pecan thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and egg yolk.
Beat well.
Add flour.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Add half pecan on top of cookie.

title: annie rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in water until all water is absorbed.
Add remaining ingredients except raisins.
Cook slowly in heavy pot 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring often.
Cook until thick, then add raisins the last 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool.
Top with cinnamon and/or nutmeg if desired.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Roll into small balls and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Melt chocolate bits and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip peanut butter balls in this, using a toothpick to hold the balls.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes about 80 buckeyes.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish and top with slices of butter.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Good with any meat dish and rice.

title: eight layer salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and rinse. Drizzle with oil; toss to coat.
Place lettuce, macaroni, eggs, salt, pepper, ham, salami and peas in that order in 2 1/2-quart trifle dish.
Combine mayo, sour cream, onions and mustard.
Spread over top.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Just before serving, sprinkle with cheese and parsley.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Arrange layers of cucumbers, onion, pepper and chives in salad bowl.
Combine vinegar, oil, sugar and salt in small saucepan. Heat to dissolve sugar; cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with chopped pimento.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream the oleo, eggs and sugars.
Mix. Add flour, cinnamon, vanilla and soda dissolved in warm water.
Mix.

Stir in chopped pecans, coconut and candy. Divide mixture into 3 or 4 parts; make each part into a roll and wrap in wax paper. Store in refrigerator. When ready to bake, slice and bake at 375° about 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: navy bean and ham soup
directions: The night before, put beans in a large bowl. Cover with water and soak overnight. The next morning, drain and put beans in a 4-quart crock-pot. Add 6 cups water, carrots, celery, potatoes, garlic powder, minced onion, salt, pepper, smoked ham, bouillon cubes and chives. Stir well. Cook on low 8 to 10 hours. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each egg.
Add flour and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg and add sugar and other ingredients.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake in greased and floured muffin tins 20 minutes at 400°.
Yields approximately 12 large muffins.

title: savory baked spaghetti
directions: In oil in large skillet, slowly cook onions and garlic for 5 minutes.
Add ground beef and brown.
Stir in salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add chili powder and water.
Break half of uncooked spaghetti into greased 2-quart casserole.
Pour on half of sauce.
Sprinkle with half of cheese. Break in rest of spaghetti and add remaining sauce and cheese. Bake, covered, at 325° for 35 minutes.
Uncover, bake 15 minutes longer or until brown.

title: german potato salad(no cook)
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Pour over the potatoes and mix.
Add more milk if more moisture is desired.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Drop by spoon on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: tangy dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill in covered container 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Yield:
1 cup. Serve with rye round.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Mix eggs, Bisquick, cheese, pepper, zucchini and onion.
Drop 2 tablespoons per round into hot oil in skillet.
Fry about 3 minutes per side.
(Line up on edges to drain instead of laying flat and they'll stay crisper.)

title: mango (fruit) bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and make a well in center. Place rest of ingredients in well and mix together.
Pour in greased pan and let set 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Hawaiian recipe.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown beef in 3 tablespoons butter.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onions and green pepper.
Spread 1/2 the cooked noodles in greased casserole.
Cover with cheese mixture. Add remaining noodles.
Pour 2 tablespoons melted butter over noodles.
Put meat mixture over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mr. parker's funnel cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Fry in at least 1 inch of oil.
Oil should be hot enough that a test drop of batter rises almost immediately to the surface.
Drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Wash and trim broccoli.
Cut into spears.
Cook broccoli, covered, about 10 minutes, until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Meanwhile, in a bowl, combine eggs, cheeses, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Arrange broccoli in a shallow baking dish. Spoon cheese mixture atop.
Stir together bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over cheese mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.
Serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: company chicken(from merry makings - vepco recipe book)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Press or process crackers in blender until finely crushed.
Melt margarine in large pan.
Spread chicken pieces with sour cream and roll in crumbs.
Lay chicken pieces in margarine and then turn buttered side up.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place potatoes in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix next 6 ingredients; pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed flakes; dribble melted butter over all.
Bake 45 minutes uncovered at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Mix all ingredients, except shredded cheese. Pour into a casserole dish. Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 30-45 minutes.

title: biscuit mix
directions: In large bowl sift dry ingredients together 3 times.
Cut in shortening.
Pack loosely in airtight container and store in fridge.
For each 1 cup mix, add 1/3 cup water; stir to blend. May also be used for pancakes by adding 1 egg.
Keeps a long time when stored in refrigerator.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat pudding with milk. Beat in ice cream.
Pour over cake; let set for 10 minutes.
Mix Jell-O with hot water.
Add strawberries. Pour over cake after it sets.
Add Cool Whip.

title: delicious chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well. Chill. Serve on leaf lettuce and garnish with 1 cup seedless grapes, i ounce Mandarin oranges, drained and 1/2 cup nuts.

title: pepper relish
directions: Heat all to boiling point and simmer for 5 minutes.
Transfer to prepared jars and seal.

title: squash-swiss cheese casserole
directions: Cut squash into 1/3-inch slices.
Place in large saucepan with onion, bay leaf, parsley and thyme.
Cover with boiling salted water and cook until barely tender.
Drain.
Remove parsley and bay leaf.
Set aside.

title: filet de boeuf a la girondine
directions: Trim a filet of beef weighing 3 1/2 to 4 pounds and rub it well with salt and pepper.
Wrap the filet with a very thin sheet of larding pork which can be obtained from your butcher (also referred to as cod fat).
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a Dutch oven; add carrots and onion, thinly sliced, and lay the filet on top of the vegetables.
Cover the pot and cook the meat for 25 to 40 minutes, turning it often to insure even cooking.
(The longer the cooking period will give well-done meat; the shorter, will give rare meat.)

Arrange the roast on a platter and surround it with a mixture of mushrooms and artichoke bottoms, sauteed in 2 tablespoons each of olive oil and butter with a small garlic clove and 2 tablespoons each of parsley and shallots, all finely chopped.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix
ingredients
and
pour into unbaked pie shells and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham salad
directions: Grind up all ingredients; mix with mayonnaise.
Refrigerate until needed.
This will make enough for 5 to 6 loaves of bread.

title: whispers(servings:  12)
directions: Place liqueurs in blender.
Fill with as much coffee ice cream as blender will hold.
Blend well.
Serve in short glasses after dinner.
Dessert, coffee and liqueur -- all in one!

title: melt away bars
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine egg yolk and remaining ingredients, except walnuts and colored sugar.
Blend well with mixer.
Stir in 1/2 cup walnuts; mix thoroughly.
Spread in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.

title: layered beef vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Saute ground beef, onions and green pepper until beef is browned. Drain fat. Add salt and mix well. Place sliced potato in bottom of 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Alternate layers of carrots, rice and meat. Pour mashed tomatoes over casserole and cover. Bake for 2 hours.

title: three-bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and oil well to dissolve the sugar; add the beans and other ingredients.
Marinate in refrigerator until thoroughly chilled.

title: easy-cheesy-potato chowder
directions: Cook until heated through.

title: almond pastry
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients as for pie.
Divide into 3 to 4 strips.
Press crosswise into three to four 2 x 10 to 12-inch strips onto a large cookie sheet, ungreased.

title: jello plum pudding
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water and while still hot, stir in Grape-Nuts, raisins, walnuts, prunes and citron (all cut fine).
Also add cinnamon and cloves.
Salt to taste.
Mix and let harden in mold.
Turn out on large plate and garnish with holly. Serve with whipped cream or pudding sauce.

title: grilled steak with balsamic vinegar
directions: Mix vinegar, original steak grilling blend and olive oil in a small bowl. Coat both sides of steaks with the mixture. Let marinate in refrigerator for about 30 minutes. Preheat grill or broiler to medium heat. Place steaks on a large sheet of aluminum foil; seal foil. Grill or broil for 20 minutes. Open foil and remove steaks and place them over direct heat; reseal foil. Continue grilling for 3 minutes per side to desired doneness. Serve immediately. Top with juice from the foil.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in butter.
Brown and crumble ground beef.
Mix all ingredients together.
Heat in a 350° oven until hot.
Serve hot.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix well and put in loaf pan.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco, sugar and powdered sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar. Mix well.
Chill
overnight.
Roll thin, cut and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix chilled juices with 1 bottle of ginger ale and sherbet in bowl until smooth.
Add remaining ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: shish-kabobs
directions: Debone meat and trim off fat.
Cut into 16 square chunks; place in marinade (Italian dressing).
Cut tomatoes, onions and peppers into 8 wedges.
Wash and remove stems from mushroom caps. Leave caps whole.
Insert meat and vegetables on skewers.
Place Shish-Kabobs over hot coals for 10 minutes, broiler 6 to 8 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: fancy baked beans
directions: Chop vegetables.
Saute vegetables and brown meat and drain. Mix all ingredients and cook on top of stove, in a crock-pot or in oven.

title: fantastic whoopie pies
directions: *Add a few drops vinegar to make sour milk.

title: jingle bells carrots
directions: Cook carrots until skin comes off.
Mix syrup made of vinegar and spices; pour over carrots.
Set overnight.
Bring to boil; remove spices and add carrots to jars.
Fill within 1/2 inch of top jar with hot spiced syrup.
Seal process in water bath.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Combine meat and onion with noodles, cheese, soup, 1 cup water, green pepper, chili sauce, pimento, salt and dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Turn into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until hot.
Serves 12.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Slice eggplant about 1/4-inch thick.
Dip each slice in beaten egg and coat lightly with bread crumbs.
In 2 1/2-quart casserole arrange in layers, starting with spaghetti sauce, eggplant, then cheeses.
Top with spaghetti sauce.
Reserve 1/2 cup combined cheeses.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheeses and bake another 15 minutes.

title: pita loaves
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour and salt. Make a well in the center and add 1 cup water, the yeast mixture and the oil. Blend, then knead for 8 to 10 minutes until smooth and elastic. Form into a 10-inch log and cut crosswise into 1-inch pieces. Knead each piece a few times. Form into balls and place 2-inches apart. Cover and let rise for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Flatten gently and roll into 6-inch rounds. Cover and let rise for 1 hour.

title: buttered carrots and celery
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes; drain.
Add 2 tablespoons butter, tossing to coat.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender or 2 knives until mix resembles coarse meal.
Store in a tightly covered container in a cool dry place.
Label and date.
Makes about 9 cups.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook slowly about 15 minutes.
Use sauce to baste chicken.
The remainder of the sauce may be served with the barbecued chicken.
If the sauce is allowed to cool down slightly, it congeals and adheres to chicken more rapidly.
Makes enough for 2 chickens.

title: oreo pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a baked pie shell. Freeze for 6 hours before serving.

title: toffee bars
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil, then with saltines.
Melt butter with brown sugar in a saucepan.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 5 minutes. Remove from oven; sprinkle chocolate morsels over crackers.
Allow to melt and spread chocolate evenly.
Freeze for 15 minutes.
Peel foil off bars; break apart and store in refrigerator.

title: weight watchers meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and place in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken milano
directions: Cut chicken into thin slivers and salt to taste.
Dip breasts in flour, eggs, and then crumbs.
Fry in oil until meat is tender and golden brown from both sides.
Place in baking dish.
Mix pasta sauce
and cream.
Pour over chicken and top with cheese.
Bake until sauce is heated and cheese is melted.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix Bisquick and water until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough 2-inches larger than inverted 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Ease into plate; flute edge if desired.

title: breaded fish
directions: Mix eggs, cream and vinegar.
Coat fish with flour; dip in this mixture, then cracker crumbs.
Deep fat fry.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Cut green pepper, onion, tomato and sausage in pieces and saute 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch, ginger, vinegar, soy sauce and apricot preserves; stir into sausage mixture.
Heat to thicken.
Add pineapple chunks and heat.
Serve over rice.

title: tasty sauerkraut dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in microwave 10 to 15 seconds. Serve with nacho chips.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter, add beef.
Brown well.
Add sour cream, tomato sauce, flour, salt, pepper and cooked, drained noodles. Blend well, heat through.

title: very blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and oil.
Stir until just moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
(Grease tin or line with paper.)
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: aunt hasseltine's cornmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients and add all to crust.
Bake in 300° oven about 1 hour until almost set, but still slightly shaky in center. Remove from oven and cover with another pie tin until cool.
You may add pecans or coconut to mix.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch). Arrange apples in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients with fork. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake until apples are tender and topping is golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Serve with cream or ice cream if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chili for a crowd
directions: Brown beef.
Add spices.
Stir in tomatoes, sauce and paste, sugar and salt.
Bring to boiling; simmer slowly, covered, stirring occasionally until thickened and flavors blend 40 minutes.
Add kidney beans; simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Serve over rice.
Top with onions.

title: variation for an apple pie
directions: Create your own apple pie.
Before putting on the top crust, slice an orange wafer thin with skin on and place on top of apples.
Put on top crust.
A nice flavor.

title: corn-muffin scrambler
directions: In medium skillet, over medium heat, lightly brown Canadian bacon on both sides.
Roll each bacon slice into cornucopia shape; set aside.
In small bowl, combine eggs, cream cheese and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
In clean skillet, over medium heat, melt butter. Add egg mixture and cook 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until set.
On each corn cake, place 2 tomato slices; cover with scrambled egg, dividing evenly.
Top each with bacon slice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook and brown meat; drain.
Stir in soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes, simmering for about 15 minutes, with occasional stirring to prevent sticking.
In medium size cake pan, semi-crush enough Doritos to layer entire bottom of pan.
Over top of Doritos, pour ingredients that have been simmering.
Spread evenly over Doritos. Using the remaining Doritos from bag, semi-crush them and sprinkle over top of mixture in pan.
Spread shredded cheese evenly over top of Doritos.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cranberry jell mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce mix and add the rest of the ingredients, pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into 1-inch balls (about 25) and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon sugar glaze
directions: Mix in plastic bag.
Sprinkle over No Fry or toast, buttered.

title: easy apple cobbler
directions: Place butter in baking dish and melt over low heat. While butter is melting, mix the flour and sugar in separate bowl; pour in and blend the (fruits like blueberry; blackberry also can be used) apples evenly over the batter. Pour over melted butter. Bake in preheated oven at 325° until brown (approximately 1 hour).

title: vanilla wafer crumb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9-inch layer cake pan. Cream butter and sugar well.
Stir in baking powder and crumbs. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Turn batter into pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn onto wire rack to cool.

title: arkansas saw mill meat and potatoes
directions: Make patties out of hamburger meat.
Layer patties, cut round potatoes and onions until all ingredients are used.
Cover and cook in heavy skillet on low until tender.

title: taco dip
directions: Chill.
Serve with large plain tortilla chips.

title: blender hollandaise
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth. With motor still running, gradually add 1/2 cup hot water. Blend until smooth again. Then cook over low heat or in a double boiler, stirring constantly, until consistency of custard. Serve hot or cold.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups of flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Stir in rest of flour to make a stiff batter.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, pepper and seasonings.
Tear up tortillas and place half of them in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer half of meat mixture over tortillas.
Put both cans of beans over meat, then all of cheese over beans.
Put another layer of tortillas and rest of meat mixture.
Mix cream of chicken soup and Ro-Tel in bowl and pour over meat.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: spiced up pretzels
directions: Break up pretzels in a bowl.
Pour oil over pretzels.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Sprinkle over pretzels and stir.
Bake on sheet cake pan at 250° for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes. Cool on paper towels.
Serves 8.

title: merry's canapes
directions: Toast bread on both sides lightly.
Combine mayonnaise, onions and parsley.
Spread on toast.
Cut out round of Swiss cheese to fit on toast.
Broil until cheese melts.
You can add a slice of a ripe black olive on top for decoration after broiling.
Makes about 12 to 15 canapes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach, drain well.
Add crumbs and rest of ingredients to melted butter.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Make small balls.
Put on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips and grated cheese. Place in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle potato chips and cheese over top and place in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Serves 10.
Leave in oven until serving time.

title: summer pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls on pizza tin (flatten rolls to fit tin). Mix 1/2 cup mayonnaise, 8 ounces cream cheese and 1 package dry Good Seasons herb dressing.
Spread on baked crescent rolls.
Top with olives, tomatoes, carrots, green pepper, cauliflower, broccoli, cucumber and grated cheese.

title: baked apples
directions: Use fresh sliced apples, enough for a large baking dish. Combine the remaining ingredients and put on stove. Bring to a boil.
Pour over apples and bake until done in a 350° or 400° oven.
Don't fill too full.

title: praline cookies
directions: Line a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan with foil, then cover with graham crackers.
Melt margarine in small saucepan.
Add brown sugar and heat to boiling.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the chopped pecans.
Pour or spoon over graham crackers. (May look skimpy.)
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Allow to cool before cutting.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Melt margarine; remove 3 tablespoons and toss with Rice Chex. Add onion to remaining margarine and saute.
Add cheese, soup and garlic; melt until smooth.
Stir in broccoli, almonds and 1 cup Rice Chex.
Crush remaining Rice Chex and place over the broccoli mixture that has been placed in a well-greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate bavarian torte
directions: Mix and bake according to package directions, using 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Cool for 15 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.
In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, brown sugar, vanilla and salt until fluffy.
Fold in cream.
Split each cake layer into 2 horizontal layers.
Place one on serving plate.
Spread with 1/4 of chocolate.
Repeat layers.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.

title: cheesy chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix chicken, soup,1/2 cup of the sour cream,1 cup of the cheese and 3 tablespoons of the cilantro. Spoon about 1/4 cup chicken mixture into center of tortilla, roll up.
Place seam side down, in greased 13X9-inch baking dish.
Top with salsa and remaining cheese.
Cover and bake for 25 minutes. Uncover, sprinkle with remaining cilantro.
Serve with remaining sour cream.
Makes 6 servings (2 enchiladas each).

title: fluffy fruit pie
directions: Dissolve Jello in Boiling Water, stir for 3 minutes.
Add Ice Cubes and stir until it thickens (2 to 3 mins.)
Remove any unmelted Ice.
Using a wire whip blend in Cool Whip continue until smooth.
Chill mixture in refrigerator until it becomes firm. Spoon chilled and firm mixture onto Crust and chill for 2 hours.

title: fudge
directions: Cream cheese well.
Mix in sugar.
Gradually add other ingredients.
Place in greased pan and flatten.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add milk and cream cheese; stir over low heat until cream cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot with French bread slices, whole wheat or rye bread cubes.

title: bacon ranch dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: west virginia biscuits
directions: Mix sugar, yeast, water and oil.
Add just enough flour to allow dough to be handled.
Roll out and cut.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Let stand one hour.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze immediately.

title: jam pastry
directions: Mix the first ingredients together.
Knead and roll out to fit large cookie sheet (greased).
Spread about 1 to 1 1/2 cups jam down middle.
Cut sides and fold into middle over jam.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Drizzle glaze of powdered sugar and milk over all when cooled.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach well.
Mix with crumbs, cheese, onion and spices.
Add eggs and butter.
Mix and form into balls. Freeze on a cookie sheet, then bag.
Bake, frozen, at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients and press into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Serve with Mushroom Sauce.

title: cinnamon pickles
directions: Bring the ingredients to a boil; add cukes and let set overnight.
Bring to a boil again.
Let set to room temperature. Bring to a boil again, put in jars and seal.
Makes about 10 pints.

title: elegante fillets
directions: Thaw fillets (sole, haddock, halibut or cod).
Arrange in buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Dash with pepper; dot with butter. Spread soup over fillets and sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Bake in hot oven (400°) for 25 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges. Serves about 3 or 4.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites with salt and vanilla until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar a little at a time until stiff and sugar is dissolved. Fold in coconut. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in slow oven (325°) about 20 minutes.

title: great frosting
directions: Heat milk to warm.
Put all ingredients in deep bowl and beat 6 to 8 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat eggs.
Add melted butter and buttermilk.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and sugar together, then add to the egg mixture.
Fold in the blueberries.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Beat eggs, flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in veggies and mix well.
In large skillet, heat 1/4 cup oil.
Drop batter by tablespoons into hot oil.
Cook 1 minute on each side.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° if using glass dish).
Microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwavable bowl on High for 2 minutes.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into melted chocolate mixture. Mix in eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out with fudgy crumbs.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 24 brownies.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients together and store in tightly sealed container. When ready for a cup of hot chocolate, simply put about 1/3 cup of mixture in cup and add hot water.
Stir and enjoy.

title: peanut bars
directions: Spread half of the peanuts in a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Melt the chips, milk and butter.
Remove from heat and add the marshmallows. Mix until smooth and pour into pan over peanuts. Add remaining half of peanuts.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Lightly saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Spread in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake an additional minute.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and cool.
Mix eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla until smooth.
Add nuts and put in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° until done 30 to 50 minutes.

title: grandma alice kline's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg and flavorings.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flour and dry ingredients.
Blend together into creamed mixture.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll half of dough at a time to 3/16-inch thick on lightly floured pastry cloth. Cut with cookie cutters.
Sprinkle with sugar if they will not be iced and decorated.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until delicately golden.
Makes 5 dozen (2 to 2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda, salt and cocoa together into a 9-inch square baking pan.
Make 3 wells in dry ingredients.
Pour salad oil into first well, vinegar into second well and vanilla into third well.
Pour 1 cup warm water over entire mixture.
Stir with a wooden spoon until well mixed.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Coconut or chopped nuts may be added to batter, if desired.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend pimiento cheese with well beaten egg.
Season to taste. Toast fancy shapes of bread on one side.
Spread other side with margarine and pimiento cheese mixture.
Broil until brown and puffed.
Makes 35.

title: overnight cabbage slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, celery, onions, green pepper and pimento and stir remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and pour over cabbage mixture (do not stir).
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Stir well before serving.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken in a container with a cover.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over chicken.
Marinate 24 to 48 hours. Grill or bake chicken at 400° for 45 minutes basting often with marinade.

title: brittany's orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend until frothy. Delicious!

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients in medium saucepan.
Separate eggs and beat yolks into milk.
Stir into dry ingredients and mix well. Bring to slow boil.
Stir constantly.
Add butter, and when thickened, remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 425° until lightly browned.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter in pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk in bowl.
Pour over butter, then add peaches.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Makes 1 can.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a deep baking dish.
Stir together flour and sugar.
Add milk and mix well.
Add to melted butter.
Add peaches and stir slightly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: In a large plastic bag or bowl, mix all ingredients until potatoes are coated.
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
It makes 8 servings.

title: mexican rice
directions: In skillet heat oil and butter.
Add rice and cook until light brown.
Add onion and garlic and saute until onion is tender.
Add salt, pepper, tomato sauce and water. Stir once or twice.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Do not stir or uncover.
Fluff with fork. Let sit 5 minutes.

title: hummus
directions: Put first 4
ingredients in blender or food processor. Blend until smooth.
Serve on flat plate or shallow bowl, spread out smoothly.
Top with olive oil.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Offer crackers or pita bread to dip.

title: chess squares
directions: Combine cake mix, oleo and 2 eggs; press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch
pan.
Combine
other
eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese;
pour
over
crust.
Bake
to
40 minutes at 350°. Can change cake mixes and make lemon, chocolate, or any kind of squares.

title: fudgesicles
directions: Beat all ingredients with mixer until well blended.
Pour into ice cube trays, small paper cups or frozen pop molds.
Insert wooden sticks or plastic spoons into pops for handles.
Freeze until firm (2 to 3 hours).

title: party fruit punch
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: creamed cabbage soup
directions: Simmer onion and butter until tender.
Add cabbage (chopped fine), carrots (sliced or chopped) and potatoes (diced).
Simmer, covered, stirring often, 20 minutes.
Add paprika, chicken broth, milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat to just boiling.
Reduce heat.
Add flour with water to thicken.
Add sharp cheese and let melt (optional).

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Form into little balls. Bake at 425° for 17 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Spread pie filling in pan.
Melt margarine and combine cake mix and nuts to it.
Crumble over pie filling.
Bake until light brown.

title: cauliflower in microwave
directions: Separate cauliflower in pieces and place in a Corning Ware dish with 2 to 4 tablespoons water.
Cover and microwave on High for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: curried zucchini soup
directions: Cook zucchini in butter until tender.
Add curry, cumin and chicken broth; bring to boil.
Let cool.
Puree soup mixture in food processor.
Beat in buttermilk and chill.
Combine carrot, watercress and parsley.
Top each serving of soup with this mixture.

title: pig eatin' cake
directions: Combine cake mix, mandarin oranges, eggs, and oil.
Beat on medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into three greased layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix whipped topping, pudding mix and crushed pineapple together to fill and frost cake. You do not need to frost the sides of this cake.
Garnish with extra mandarin oranges and fresh strawberries.

title: buttermilk skillet cornbread
directions: Melt butter in skillet until hot.
Mix all ingredients; add to hot skillet.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato soup with butterballs
directions: Cook onion and potatoes in water, boiling gently.
Keep covered for 15 minutes
or
until
potatoes
are tender.
Mash potatoes and onions.
Add milk and seasonings.
Heat slowly to serving temperature,
stirring
occasionally to prevent sticking. Add butterballs to thicken slightly.

title: muesli(swiss oatmeal)
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.
Mix well.
Serve with milk and honey, if desired.
May be warmed in microwave, if desired.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring to boil; boil until liquid spins a thread.
Add 2 cups raw Spanish peanuts and boil until it turns a golden brown. Remove from heat and add 2 tablespoons butter or margarine and 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Stir quickly and carefully as liquid will splatter.
Quickly add 2 teaspoons baking soda and spread on buttered cookie sheet.

title: key lime pie
directions: In large heat resistant bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
With wire whisk, stir in yogurt.
With wooden spoon, fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: pine bark
directions: Line
cookie sheet with foil and place saltines on foil to form a solid layer.
Bring brown sugar and butter to a boil (3 minutes).
Pour over crackers.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, nuts and vanilla; mix well. Spoon melted butter into greased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows over cake (hot); cover with frosting.

title: real good dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Drain.
Add cheese and soup. Heat over low temperature until cheese is melted and thoroughly blended.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Make lime jello according to package directions.
Pour into a 14 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until partly set.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup hot water in top of double boiler.
Add marshmallows and stir to melt.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup drained pineapple juice and cream cheese.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in pineapple.
Cool slightly.
Fold in whipped cream and mayo.
Chill until thick.
Pour in layer over lime jello.
Chill until almost set.
Prepare cherry jello according to package directions.
Chill until syrupy.
Pour over pineapple layer.
Chill until firm.
Makes 24 servings.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt margarine.
Let it roll over casserole surface.
Add macaroni, cottage and Cheddar cheeses.
Pour over this 2 1/4 cups boiling water.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs; gradually beat in sugar, then oil.
Combine dry ingredients; add to first mixture alternately with zucchini. Stir in raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Pour in 2 greased and lightly floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: pudding cake(reduced calorie)
directions: Combine margarine, flour and pecans for crust; press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.

title: carrots in wine
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add raw carrots and grated onion. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add dry white wine.
Cover and cook over low heat, about 15 minutes until carrots are tender.
Add parsley, optional.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine eggs, milk, vanilla, cinnamon and salt. Stir in bread cubes.
Stir in sugar and raisins.
Pour mixture into an 8-inch round glass ovenware dish.
Place dish in a large shallow pan on oven rack.
Pour hot water into pan 1-inch deep.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Can be served with the following Vanilla Sauce.

title: overnight cucumber pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Put all ingredients, except cucumbers, in 1/2 gallon jar.
Cover and shake or stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pack cucumbers in and chill overnight.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix milk and instant pudding;
beat until thick.
Put in Cool Whip
and
mix.
Butter bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place layer of graham crackers over bottom; pour one-half of pudding, then another
layer of crackers.
Pour the rest of pudding and then layer of crackers.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Then spread chocolate
icing on top of last layer of crackers.
Jiffy icing works okay.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: hush puppy appetizers
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. In a separate bowl, mix egg, milk and onion.

title: regal cheesecake
directions: Combine sugar, crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-from pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, flour and vanilla, mixing well at medium speed on electric mixer.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in sour cream; pour over crust.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan.
Chill.
Spoon your favorite topping over the cheesecake.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased loaf pan.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt chocolate squares and margarine over medium heat. Remove. Add other ingredients, except nuts.
Beat until smooth. Add nuts.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and store in refrigerator.

title: kitty's pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed. Bring shrimp to boil. Peel and cut up vegetables (you can substitute the vegetables your family likes).

title: chilled strawberry delight
directions: Line a 12 x 7-inch pan with half the crumbs.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, salt and eggs, one a a time.
Keep beating to increase volume.
Spread over crumbs; place sliced berries on top, then unsweetened cream, whipped stiff.
Place remaining crumbs on top.
Chill overnight.

title: apple pie special
directions: For fluffy, fresh and flavorful, try adding honey to whipped topping mix before whipping.
You can be sure the topping won't wilt as it crowns your pie with flavor enticement.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups topping.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Place Pepperidge Farm (1/2 package) on bottom of 2-quart casserole dish, then add deboned chicken on top.
Then pour 1 can cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soup plus 2 cans broth from chicken.
Spread 1/2 package Pepperidge Farm on top.
Cook at 400° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and oleo together until smooth.
Stir constantly to keep from scorching.
Put Corn Chex in large bowl and pour the melted chocolate mixture over the Chex and toss until all are covered.
Put in grocery sack.
Add powdered sugar, then put the chocolate covered Chex into bag and shake well.
Let cool.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Combine crumbs and 2 tablespoons of butter; set aside.
Add onion to remaining butter and saute over low heat.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk.
Increase heat to medium; cook until bubbly and thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese; stir until smooth.
Stir in carrots and parsley flakes.
Spread in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumb mixture. Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until bubbly and crumbs are golden brown.

title: taco salad soup
directions: Brown meat with onion and pepper. Add all other ingredients and simmer 1 hour. Serve with crushed tortilla chips and grated cheese.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the first 3 items; fold in peanut butter and Cool Whip. Fill pie crusts and freeze.
Serve while partially frozen.
Makes 2 pies.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Using food processor, chop apples; put in large bowl. Chop nuts in same way and combine with apples. Add raisins to the apples and nuts. Set aside. Place eggs, shortening, sugar and vanilla in mixer and mix until ingredients are well blended. Add cinnamon, baking soda and salt. Add flour slowly until ingredients are barely mixed. Pour batter into apples, raisins and nuts. Stir well. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain frozen vegetables.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread onion evenly over vegetables.
In small bowl, combine soup, cheese and sour cream; blend well.
Season with salt and pepper; pour over vegetables.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over top of casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover; bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 16 servings.

title: betty's rice
directions: Mix all ingredients well together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dad's cookies
directions: Combine all and drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: wild rice chicken supreme
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Saute onion in melted butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in half and half and chicken broth.
Cook until thick.
Mix sauce with chicken, pimento, parsley and almonds.
Bake 45 minutes, uncovered, at 425°.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: In shallow bowl, beat egg. Dip chicken. Roll in bread crumbs. Spray 9-inch nonstick skillet with Pam. Add chicken and cook over medium heat until golden brown, about 3 minutes each side. Top each cutlet with tomato sauce and cheese. Cover skillet and cook until cheese is melted, about 1 minute.

title: kit kat bars
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with Waverly or Club House crackers. Boil crushed graham crackers, brown sugar, sugar, milk and butter or margarine for 5 minutes.
Spread 1/2 of the mixture on the crackers.
Put another layer of Waverly or Club House crackers and then the rest of the mixture.
Top with another layer of Waverly or Club House crackers, then frost with melted chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Makes approximately 24 (2-inch) squares.

title: noodles
directions: Measure flour onto tabletop.
Sprinkle salt over flour.
Mix in and make a well in the center.
Break eggs into well.
Mix with a fork, gradually adding the flour.
When dough starts to stick to the fork, continue mixing with hands.
Knead dough about 15 times. Let rest while you wash your hands.

title: lentil soup
directions: Soak lentils overnight in 2 quarts water.
Simmer 45 minutes until lentils are tender.
Skim off scum that rises to top.
Add all other ingredients except lemon and simmer together 1 to 2 hours until everything is tender and flavors are blended.
Squeeze juice from lemon and add to soup.
Serve with a dollop of sour cream.
Freezes well.

title: pretzel pie
directions: In blender, crush pretzels (or in a plastic bag, crush with a rolling pin).
Mix crumbs, sugar and butter until blended.
Form a crust in a 9-inch pie pan and bake at 375° for about 8 minutes. Cool or freeze.

title: fudgy scotch ring
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch morsels with sweetened condensed milk in top of double boiler over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir occasionally until morsels melt and mixture begins to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Add chopped walnuts and vanilla. Blend well.
Chill for about 1 hour or until mixture thickens. Line bottom of a 9-inch pie pan with a 12-inch square of foil. Place 3/4 cup walnut halves in bottom of pan, forming a 2-inch wide flat ring.
Spoon chocolate mixture in small mounds on top of nuts to form ring.
Decorate with remaining nuts.
Add maraschino cherries, if desired.
Chill in refrigerator until firm enough to slice.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Makes about 36 slices.

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix baking soda and water together and pour over raisins.
Let stand overnight, without stirring.
Next morning, sift together the flour, sugar and salt.
Stir this into the raisin mixture with a spoon.
Add oil and continue to mix well with a spoon.
Batter will be thick.

title: karen leonard's spice cookies
directions: Sift and measure flour; add salt, cream of tarter, baking soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Sift together.
In separate bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add 1 egg and beat until creamy. Stir in milk and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Chill in refrigerator about 2 hours or until easy to handle.
Roll dough on floured surface to 1/4-inch or 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush cut outs with beaten egg white and sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes until tender.
Cool, peel and shred coarsely.
Heat butter in saucepan; remove from heat.
Add cheese, stirring in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes. Place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
dish.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: cabbage cheese casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water until nearly done.
Reserve the water.
Place cabbage in baking dish.
Add sauce to drained cabbage.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan and saute vegetables until soft and light brown.
Combine all ingredients and bake 45 minutes uncovered.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together well and form into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: unstuffed cabbage italian
directions: Brown rice and set aside.
Brown beef, onion, salt and pepper. Add rice, then stir in half of cheese.
Mix all together.
In a greased casserole, layer cabbage and meat mixture until all are used.
Combine tomato sauce and water; pour over top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. More meat, sauce and cheese may be used, if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first five ingredients plus 1/4 cup of the pecans. Shape into ball; refrigerate until firm. Roll in remaining pecans.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: In a double boiler, combine all of the ingredients except vanilla.
Stir well; beat at high speed over boiling water (keeping water from touching bottom of pan), until frosting forms soft peaks.
Remove from boiler; continue to beat on low speed until cool and frosting forms stiff peaks, 3 to 4 minutes.

title: white trash
directions: Melt the chocolate and oil together.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour the chocolate mixture over it and coat well.
Spread the mixture thinly on waxed paper and let dry well.
Break the pieces and store in a tightly covered container.

title: fluffy dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together in mixing bowl. Combine milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut.*
Put dumplings in boiling liquid.
Cover.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat.
Don't lift cover.
Simmer 12 to 15 minutes.

title: maraschino nut bread
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs, sugar and cherry juice; add to dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly; fold in nuts and cherries.
Pour into waxed paper lined loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: peaches and cream cookies
directions: Dip cookie in vermouth; drain on paper towel (not dry).
Roll in granulated sugar.
Make a leaf on top.
Put in medium size cupcake paper cups.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook hen until tender, adding more water when needed.
Add salt and pepper.
Debone chicken.

title: baked green beans
directions: Cut string beans to 1/2-inch pieces.
Add other ingredients. Place in baking dish.
Add 1/4 cup of water.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: clay
directions: Combine cornstarch and soda in saucepan.
Cook on medium until it boils and is a clay like consistency.
Knead on cornstarch dusted surface.
When cool enough to handle, cover with damp cloth and cool. Store in plastic bag in cool place. Form into shapes. Can be baked at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel potatoes and cut up like French fries.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with first 5 ingredients.
Add butter.
Twist slices of lemon and add lemon peel.
Add water and bake at 400° for about 1 hour.
Baste often.

title: peanut-butter cookies
directions: Mix and make into balls.
Press with fork or glass bottom. Bake 12 minutes in quick oven at 375°.
Makes 8 to 9 dozen cookies.

title: barbecued t.v.p. balls
directions: *T.V.P. - Textured Vegetable Protein

title: potato candy
directions: Mash potato until it is almost liquid.
Add vanilla; mix.
Add 10x sugar until mixture is of a consistency where it can be rolled easily.
Roll the mixture.
Spread peanut butter on top.
Roll up like a jelly roll then cut into small pieces.

title: cajun spaghetti
directions: Brown in nonstick pan separately ground beef, smoked sausage and Jimmy Dean sausage.
Chop onion, bell pepper, garlic cloves and jalapeno peppers.
Saute vegetables in olive oil and Creole seasoning.

In large nonstick cooker with lid over medium heat, put stewed tomatoes, whole tomatoes, tomato sauce and chicken broth. Bring heat to medium-high and add meat, mushrooms and vegetables. Let mixture come to a bubble.
Take spaghetti noodles and break into thirds.
When mixture begins to boil, slowly add noodles. When everything is in cooker, cover and cook on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Every 5 minutes turn stove down one notch and cook for 5 more minutes.
Total cooking should be around 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
When finished, cover mixture with Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese.
Cover and let stand for 10 minutes.
Great with garlic bread and salad.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt margarine in an ovenproof dish; set aside.
Pour buttermilk into a shallow dish.
Pour the Bisquick in a shallow dish.
Dip chicken in buttermilk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Roll chicken in Bisquick and place in ovenproof dish.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Turn.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Serve.

title: toasted butter-pecan cake(mrs. colley e. pittman)
directions: Toast pecans in 1/4 cup butter in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir frequently.

Sift flour with baking powder and salt. Set aside. Cream remaining butter. Gradually add sugar, creaming well. Blend in one egg at a time, beating well after last egg. Alternately add dry ingredients and milk. Stir in vanilla and 1 1/3 cups pecans.
Reserve remaining pecans for frosting.
Turn into three 8 or 9-inch round layer pans, well-greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Pour off excess fat.
Mix well with other ingredients.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Spoon on buns.
Serve immediately.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Brush chicken pieces with French dressing; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange chicken skin side down in a shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Drain syrup from pineapple into a small dish.
Reserve pineapple.
Add chicken broth and soy sauce to pineapple.
Mix lemon juice with cornstarch; add to pineapple mixture.
Return to 450° and bake about 30 minutes or until chicken is browned (be sure to baste chicken with mixture).

Cook pea pods (as directions on package). Just before serving, combine cooked pea pods, drained water chestnuts, pineapple and onions with chicken and leave in oven for a few minutes to allow mixture to heat.

title: banana punch
directions: Heat sugar and water until melted.
Cool.
(This equals 8 cups liquid.)
Add pineapple-grapefruit juice, orange juice and bananas. Freeze in one-quart containers.
(Makes 7 quarts.)
At serving time, add equal parts ginger ale to crushed frozen punch.
Great for parties and receptions.
Absolutely yummy!

title: "salsa"(dip)
directions: Peel tomatoes first and cut up.
Then add garlic, onions, green peppers, vinegar, pinch of cayenne pepper and tomato paste. Bring all of this to a boil for about 15 minutes.
Then add jalapeno peppers and cook for 1 hour.
Then pack in jars and seal.

title: vegetable-olive salad
directions: Cut up all ingredients, then mix with mayonnaise.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until tender,
leave
broth
and cook spaghetti in this.
Saute
in
butter
the
onion and bell pepper until tender.
Place all ingredients in pot with spaghetti and simmer. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli and lima bean casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and limas until tender; drain.
Mix all ingredients together except for margarine and bread crumbs.
Pour into a greased casserole and dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: plain cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown; let cool.

title: dottie's stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut tops off bell peppers and remove seeds.
Stand upright in small amount of salted water and boil until just tender.
Drain and set aside to cool.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg. Add cinnamon and soda to flour and sift. Add milk and flour mix to creamed sugar and butter. Fold in fruit. Grease cookie sheet. Drop by heaping teaspoon on cookie sheet. Cook at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix butter with hot raisins.
Mix sugar, eggs and lemon juice. Add
raisin
mixture, then pecans.
Add vanilla.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese, ham and potato casserole
directions: Cook whole potatoes.
Peel and cube.
Combine other ingredients.
Pour into Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and melted butter.
In a separate bowl, add milk to dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts to batter.
Mix and pour into a 5 x 7-inch greased pan.
Pour cocoa sauce over batter.
Bake in 300° oven for approximately 45 minutes.
Leave in pan. Cut into 10 small squares. When cool, remove and turn upside down on plate.
Serve cold with sweetened flavored whipped cream.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix eggs, flour and sugars well; add both corns.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Remove and sprinkle cracker mixture (soft butter and crackers) over top.
When pudding doesn't wobble, cook for another 15 minutes.

title: hot sausage appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients
in
large
mixing bowl.
Shape into 1-inch balls and
place
on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
These can be prepared ahead and frozen. Allow to reach room temperature and then bake.

title: old-fashioned sour cream cookies
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture alternately with sour cream.
Divide dough; roll out to 1/4-inch thick on well floured pastry cloth (counter is fine).
Cut with 2-inch cutter. Place on greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: fudge nut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and milk. Add eggs.
Cook over medium heat until thick. Take off heat and add butter, vanilla and nuts. Pour into shell and cool. Add whipped topping.

title: hot fudge ice cream topping
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Blend in sugar and salt.
Slowly stir in milk.
Cook until hot, stirring constantly, but do not bring to boil.
(I usually start to add milk alternately with the sugar after adding a couple cups of sugar.)

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Mold into two rolls and wrap in wax paper.
Place in refrigerator until ready to use.
Slice.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Separate cabbage
leaves and wilt in 3 to 4 cups of hot water. Mix
meat,
rice,	onion,	salt
and pepper into small balls. Wrap
in
cabbage
leaves.	Place
closely in roaster. Cover with water
and	tomato	juice.	Bake
2 hours at 350°. Before serving, add milk.

title: joyce's hot rolls(refrigerator dough)
directions: Put flour in large mixing bowl with shortening, salt and 1/2 of sugar.
Mix very good.
Put 4 1/2 cups warm water in another mixing bowl with other 1/2 of sugar and 3 packages of yeast to rise.
Beat 5 eggs up and gently stir into yeast and water mixture.
Then mix the two mixtures together; work it in with your hands and knead, knead, knead, adding flour enough to keep hands from being sticky (the more you knead, the better the rolls).
Place in a bowl with an airtight lid.
Pinch off what you need to make rolls.
Keep refrigerated.
Make into rolls on greased pan and let raise until light looking and bake at 350° until done.
Will keep for a week or more in airtight bowl in refrigerator.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese, stir in pineapple, 1 cup nuts, green pepper, etc.
Chill.
Form into two balls and roll in rest of nuts.

title: hawaiian pork chops(diabetic; low sugar.)
directions: In large skillet, sprayed with vegetable pan spray, cook onion and green pepper until tender. Remove from skillet. Mix flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag. Add chops one at a time; shake to coat meat. Brown chops in skillet. Place pineapple slice on top of each chop. Sprinkle with onion and green pepper. Combine vinegar, catsup and juice to make sauce. Pour over chops. Simmer 4 minutes, until chops are tender.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: one bowl chocolate pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coarsely chop 4 squares of the chocolate and set aside.
Line 9-inch pie plate as directed on package with pie crust.
Microwave remaining 4 squares of chocolate and butter in large microwaveable bowl on High 1 to 2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted. Brush bottom of pie crust with small amount of beaten egg.
Stir sugar, corn syrup, eggs and vanilla into chocolate mixture until well blended.
Stir in pecans or walnuts and chopped chocolate.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 55 minutes or until knife inserted 2-inches from edge comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy apple coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter bottom of 10 1/4 x 15 1/4 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Beat pie filling with eggs in large bowl. Stir in cake mix; beat well.
Turn batter into prepared pan, spreading evenly.
Top with nuts.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl; mix well.
Sprinkle over nuts.
Bake 35 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Cut into squares; serve warm. This cake freezes well.

title: potato casserole
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Slice potatoes and onion thin.
Mix soups and water.
Spread a thin layer of soup mixture in bottom of casserole dish, then a layer of potatoes and onion.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Layer again as preceding. Place in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Spread with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: lemon squares
directions: Blend butter, 2 cups flour, 10x sugar and salt.
Press into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Cool for 5 minutes.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Dice all vegetables fairly small into large bowl.
Add mozzarella, salami, olives and pepperoncini (with a couple of ounces of juice from pepperoncini, adds extra zing!).
Toss everything and add dressing to taste.

title: mint balls
directions: Cream the sugar, milk and peppermint; roll into balls.
Place on waxed paper lined tray.
Insert toothpicks into each ball. Chill.
Melt wax and chips.
Dip balls into wax mixture.
Place back on tray to cool.

title: bacon-wrapped baked chicken
directions: Wrap chicken breasts in strips of bacon, laying in large casserole dish.
Cover with chopped up butter pieces.
Mix soups with 1 cup water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice and cook zucchini in a small amount of water.
Drain thoroughly and mash.
Mix into the other ingredients.
Top with cheese and bake at 300° for 30 minutes (until top is golden and bubbly).

title: tomato gravy and biscuits
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan.
Add flour to pan over medium heat and stir constantly until light brown.
Add tomatoes and 1 can of water; stir well and add more water as needed while simmering.
Serve hot over biscuits.
Serves 2 heartily with leftovers.

title: black forest cherry cake(serves 10)
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in 1-quart saucepan.
Add enough water to reserved liquid to measure 3/4 cup; stir into sugar mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir one minute.
Stir in Kirsch and food coloring.
Cut cherries in halves; stir into filling.
Refrigerate until completely chilled.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Measure 1 cup water into liquid measuring cup; microwave for 3 minutes.
Add 1 bouillon cube to water.
Dice chicken and place in small Baggie.
Peel and slice the carrots.
In round glass baking pan or 2-quart casserole, combine broccoli, carrots and broth. Microwave 5 to 7 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender, stirring once.
Place ingredients from round glass baking pan into kettle for stove top cooking.
Add diced chicken and shredded cheese to pot.
In a small bowl, stir 1/4 cup flour with 1/2 cup cold water until smooth.
Stir into the pot; cook over medium heat on stove until thick and bubbly, stirring every few minutes, or microwave 5 to 8 minutes, stirring every minute.
Ladle into soup bowls and serve.

title: coconut fried shrimp
directions: Split and flatten shrimp.
Sift dry ingredients; add milk and egg.
Dip shrimp in batter; roll in coconut.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: doodle cake
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry crazy cake
directions: Line bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13 pan with large marshmallows, leaving space between marshmallows.
Too many marshmallows placed too close together will cause the cake to bake over the sides.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Pour cake batter over marshmallows.
Mix dry jello into the pie filling and spread over cake batter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes. Let cool and then dust with powdered sugar.
