title: million dollar apple pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Pour over prepared apples.
Mix vanilla with brown sugar and pour over apples.
Cover with top crust, pierce top.
Put foil on rim of crust until last 10 minutes of baking.
Always put foil under pie in oven to catch any runover.
Bake at 425° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Coat chicken in seasoned flour.
Dip in melted margarine.
Add additional margarine, if needed, and cook about 1/2 hour in a foil lined pan in 375° oven.
Turn and cook about another 30 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: sin cake
directions: Blend butter, flour and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.
Next blend cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over the first layer, then mix pudding and milk.
Pour over the cake.
Top with Cool Whip and pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: sun pickles
directions: Bring water, vinegar and kosher salt to a boil and cool.
Put cukes in jar with dill tops, garlic and alum.
Cover with water mixture.
Place slice of bread on top of cukes.
Cover with foil. Set in sunlight for 3 days.
Remove bread.
Replace with lid.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: philadelphia cream cheese salad
directions: Heat pineapple in juice to boiling.
Add the package of jello; stir well.
Cream the cream cheese.
Combine with the pineapple and jello mixture while it's warm; let cool.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix first three ingredients until soft dough forms.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8-10 minutes at 450°.
Combine the remaining ingredients and brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.
Makes 10-12 biscuits.

title: strawberry yum yum
directions: In a square baking dish, crumble package of cookies and mix with butter. Press cookies to bottom of pan to make a crust.

title: five bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and set aside.
In bacon grease, fry onions with brown sugar (20 minutes; watch).
Before frying, add salt, garlic powder and mustard to onions.
Drain and add beans.
Mix together; put into casserole and add crumbled bacon to top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and cheese. Spread over other ingredients.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: cheesy cauliflower bake
directions: Cut cauliflower into pieces. Cook until crisp-tender. Layer in buttered casserole dish. Combine cream of mushroom soup and 1 can of milk until smooth. Pour over cauliflower. Top with cheese. Pour Bisquick on top of cheese and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable-ham casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, onions, water chestnuts, cheese, mayonnaise and ham.
Pour into casserole dish; top with crackers mixed with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wonderful molasses cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Add dry ingredients, hand mix all together.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Combine rice, beef, salt, pepper, minced onion and 4 tablespoons tomato soup.
Make meatballs.
Add rest of tomato soup and water.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes and with the tomato soup gravy.

title: chopped ham for sandwiches or dip
directions: Put meat through grinder and add mayonnaise.

title: creamy banana pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; set aside.
In a saucepan combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Blend in the milk and egg yolks; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from the heat; stir in softened gelatin until dissolved.
Stir in butter and vanilla. Cover the surface of custard with plastic wrap and chill until no longer warm.
Slice 3 bananas; fold into custard with whipped cream.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill until set, about 4 to 5 hours.

title: baked grated carrots
directions: Bake carrots in covered casserole for 30 minutes at 325°.
Do not add water.
Remove from oven.
Add butter and seasonings. Serve.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple on bottom layer (keep juice and put in later). Spread pie mix over pineapple.
Spread cake mix over cherry mix. Cut margarine in small squares over cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans over all and bake until brown at 375°.
Turn down to 300° as it browns and bake for 45 minutes.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Grate cheese and mix in all other ingredients. To make it real smooth, it may be done in a mixer.

title: hot! sauce
directions: Mix together with electric mixer on low speed.
Store in refrigerator.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Combine spaghetti, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Place half of the mixture in a greased baking dish.
Add half the Mozzarella cheese. Repeat with remaining spaghetti and Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 325° for about 25 to 35 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes. Cut in squares and serve with spaghetti sauce. Serves 4.

title: dirt cake or sand
directions: You will need an 8-inch flowerpot and silk flowers (optional).

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook all but coconut in double boiler until thick.
Add coconut and pour in baked crust.
Add meringue and brown.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender.
Mix all ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Peel
and grate cucumber.
Grate onion.
Put in strainer and press
out
juice.
Combine with cream cheese.
Mix mayonnaise to mixture of spreading consistency.
Salt to taste.
May be used as sandwich or with crackers.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix with other ingredients.
Store in covered bowl in refrigerator and use as desired.
This batter will keep several days.

title: cranberry fizz
directions: Combine juices and sugar well.
Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Makes 16 1/2 cups.

title: biscuit barbecups
directions: Grease 10 muffin cups.
Brown ground beef in large skillet; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Place 1 biscuit in each greased muffin cup; firmly press in bottom and up sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat mixture into each biscuit.
Sprinkle each with cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges of biscuits are golden brown.
Cook 1 minute; remove from pan.
Yields 10 servings.

title: picante sauce
directions: Position knife blade in food processor.
Add onion, jalapeno peppers and garlic.
Pulse 3 to 4 times or until mixture is chopped.
Add tomatoes and process until blended.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk. Stir, bringing to a boil.
Start timing at full boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Pour onto greased tray. Chill at once.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and chicken in butter.
Add remaining ingredients in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook celery and onions until tender.
Mix all ingredients except chow mein noodles.
Pour into a large baking dish.
Top with chow mein noodles and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Cut creamed cheese into small pieces.
Melt it, the chocolate squares and the milk together.
Beat in powdered sugar until smooth.

title: salad esmeralda
directions: Thinly slice zucchini.
Pour Italian dressing over zucchini. Marinate 30 minutes.
Cut cream cheese into small cubes.
Fry bacon in skillet over high heat until crisp.
Drain on paper towel. Crumble.
Add all ingredients to the salad bowl.
Toss gently until well mixed.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except crackers and butter. Crush crackers and melt butter.
Pour over mixture and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly.

title: shrimp and rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and cool in refrigerator.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients except nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
After slightly baking, sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350° until center of pie is not as firm as rest of pie.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix dissolved yeast, sugar, eggs and warm water.
Add oil, salt and flour.
Let stand 8 hours or overnight.
Punch down; knead slightly and form into rolls.
Let rise 6 hours.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: cherry delight
directions: Add to graham cracker crumbs, 1 tablespoon sugar and melted butter.
Mix and pat into bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: macaroni pizza
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese dinner as usual, then add eggs and put on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream well the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Drop rounded teaspoonful about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until delicately browned, 8 to 10 minutes. Remove to cooling racks.
Yields 5 dozen (2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, add oil, flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and grated zucchini.
Fold in nuts. Pour into greased pans (fill to 1/2 full).
Cook for 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: holiday ham and cheese ball
directions: In a small bowl, combine Cheddar, cream cheese, deviled ham, scallions and chiles; mix well.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in plastic and chill.
Remove from refrigerator to soften slightly before serving.
Makes a 2-cup cheese ball.

title: railroad meat pie
directions: Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Combine 2 small packages corn bread mix with 1 tablespoon onion flakes.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Grate cheese and sprinkle over if you like.

title: grape-nut pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.
Stir 2 or 3 times during baking time so Grape-Nuts won't stay on bottom of pudding only.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: cherry crunch pie* * * * *
directions: Served this to some ladies during a stitch-in.
One was from Oklahoma and did not care for crab.
She complimented me on it and didn't realize there was crab in it.

title: spicy meat loaf
directions: Add all the ingredients to the ground beef.
Mix together. Place into a baking pan.
Cook for an hour at 350°.
When done, cover with cheese.

title: happy bread
directions: Have
all ingredients at room temperature, except where otherwise indicated.

title: party jello
directions: Mix well. Refrigerate before serving.

title: chicken creole
directions: In large skillet, saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms until onion is soft.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: mrs. fields cookies
directions: Cream
together
margarine, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla,
flour, oatmeal, salt, soda and baking powder. Mix together
all ingredients and add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and chopped nuts.

title: mom's chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, butter, vanilla and coffee in large mixing bowl.
In separate bowl, sift together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add sifted flour mixture to the sugar mixture until blended.
Finally add boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: mulled cider
directions: Slowly bring cider to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Strain to remove spices.
Pour cider over clove studded orange slices.

title: o'brien potatoes
directions: Crumble first five ingredients.
Pour butter over the top. Stir.
Put in casserole and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: bread pudding
directions: Grease bowl or pan (put into another pan with hot water).
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: josh and rachel's kiss surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease Bundt pan or ring mold with shortening or butter.
Melt margarine.
Separate biscuits and flatten each into a 3-inch circle.
Unwrap kisses and place 1 into center of each biscuit circle.
Wrap biscuit around kiss, pinching edges to seal firmly.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Dip each ball into melted margarine and then sugar mixture.
Arrange balls in 2 layers in pan, placing balls in second layer between balls in first layer.
Bake 20 minutes until golden brown and then cool 1 minute.
Turn mold upside-down on plate.
Cool 10 minutes and serve warm.

title: homemade chicken pie
directions: Saute mushrooms, sprinkled with garlic powder, in butter. Blend cornstarch and milk; add to mushrooms.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Continue cooking 1 minute longer. Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into pastry lined deep dish pie plate.
Top with second crust; seal edges with fork.
Cut steam vents in top.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, or until browned.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine shortening and sugar; beat until creamy.
Then add eggs, one at a time.
Add lemon flavoring and milk.
Beat and add the flour.
Add pinch of salt.
Beat until smooth.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: mallimation cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg whites and beat well.
Add flour and baking powder mixture, alternating with milk.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemony angel cake(fat-free)
directions: Prepare cake mix, bake and cool, following package directions.

title: oven-baked chicken with mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Skin the chicken; cut into 2 legs, 2 thighs, and 4 breast pieces.
Lay each piece of chicken on a bacon slice; sprinkle half the mushrooms over the chicken.
Season each portion with pepper.
Roll bacon around chicken; secure with toothpicks.
Grease a shallow baking dish with 1/4 cup butter. Place the bacon-wrapped chicken portions in the baking dish; dot with small pieces of remaining butter.
Sprinkle with salt. Cover.
Bake on middle shelf for 1 hour, basting occasionally. Remove cover; bake for 15 minutes longer or until bacon is brown. Place chicken portions on heated serving dish; cover.
Keep warm.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients one at a time until just mixed.
Spread into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lime meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and water.
Cook and stir until thick and transparent. Separate the eggs and put whites aside. Add cornstarch mixture to egg yolks.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add butter, grated lime rind and lime juice.
Pour into the pie shell. Top with meringue made from the 3 egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar beaten until stiff.
Bake a few minutes to brown.

title: grandmother's pear marmalade
directions: Grind pears in meat grinder.
Mix pears, sugar and lemon juice.
Cook 1 hour.
Add pineapple.
Cook 1 hour longer.
May use food processor. Yield:
5 quarts.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Soak peas overnight.
Drain; cover with fresh water.
Add other ingredients.
Cook until peas are done.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream Crisco, sugar and salt; add beaten egg, yeast water and warm milk.
Mix enough plain flour to mixture to make soft dough.
Knead well.
Place in greased bowl and refrigerate until ready to use.
Make rolls and let rise until double in size.
Cook.

title: deep sea potage
directions: Heat in saucepan and stir occasionally.
Makes 6 1/2 cups.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased baking dish. Combine cranberry sauce, onion soup and dressing; mix well.
Pour sauce over chicken and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Bake, covered, in 350° gas oven 1 hour.
Remove cover; bake an additional 20 minutes or until tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix sugar, vinegar, vanilla, milk and eggs with margarine.
Mix well.
Add coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook until golden brown at about 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Doubled, makes 3 small pies.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add taco seasoning.
Mix according to package.
When cooked, set aside. In large salad bowl, make salad out of vegetables.
Add Catalina salad dressing and hamburger meat.
Toss.
Sprinkle cheese and naco chips (crushed) on top.

title: peanut butter delight cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in saucepan and bring to a boil for 2 minutes; remove form heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: williamsburg bread
directions: Grease a 9x13 inch pan.
Roll out crescent rolls (1 can) on bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk with mixer until creamy.
Spread on top of crescent rolls.
Place 2nd roll of crescent rolls on top of mixture.
Mix egg white, brush on top of crescent roll.
Mix 1 teaspoon of cinnamon to a cup of sugar.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter until well blended.
Add granulated sugar and brown sugar; beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients and then chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey oriental
directions: Saute mushrooms, celery, onion and green pepper in oil just until tender.
Stir in broth, cornstarch and 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Cook, stirring frequently, until thickened.
Add turkey and water chestnuts; heat thoroughly.
Serve with Chinese noodles and soy sauce, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla together.
Mix heavy whipping cream as per instructions on package.
Fold whipping cream into other mixture and put into graham cracker crust.
Chill 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
Add ketchup, chili powder and oregano; simmer.
In large bowl place lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Add meat mixture.
Mix together the taco sauce and mayonnaise.
Pour over lettuce mix.
Mix all ingredients together and top with crushed Fritos right before serving.

title: chicken bones
directions: Mix and roll finger-sized.
Roll in crushed cornflakes.
Cut in inch lengths and roll ends in cornflakes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Stir in oats in water, remove from heat, cover and let stand 20 min.
Cream sugar, brown sugar, margarine, and eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients, nuts, and vanilla.
Bake at 350°F for 30-40 min.

title: chow-chow
directions: Mix cabbage, peppers, onions together with salt.
Let set two hours.
Mix other ingredients, pour over cabbage and let simmer 20 minutes.

title: orange dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into blender or food processor except salad oil.
With steel blade in place, turn on machine and slowly drizzle in 3/4 cup salad oil to make a smooth, homogenized, but slightly runny dressing.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups dressing.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, powdered sugar and flour.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Roll in balls.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes. Before cookies cool, dust with powdered sugar.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water, vinegar, salt and pepper; chill.
When slightly thickened, add cucumber and onion.
Turn into individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Makes a full six or twelve half molds.
Especially good to serve with ham.

title: pound cake delight(always a winner)
directions: Mix the first six ingredients and set aside for top.
In separate bowl mix remaining ingredients for bottom.
Butter loaf pan.
Sprinkle bottom of pan with bottom mixture.
Pour remaining ingredients on top.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together water, sugar, Jell-O, cornstarch and salt.
Cook together until mixture turns clear, stirring as it thickens.
Cool. Spoon
into baked pie crusts lined with sliced berries.
Chill. Serve with topping or whipped cream.

title: healthy cookies
directions: Beat margarine with electric mixer.
Gradually add sugars; beat well after each addition.
Add Egg Beaters and vanilla.
Mix. In a separate bowl, combine flour, soda and oats.
Gradually add to bowl of other ingredients, stirring well after each addition. Stir in raisins.
Spray cookie sheets with vegetable oil spray. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Let cool.

title: three day punch
directions: Set first 6 ingredients for 2 or 3 days.
Add red food coloring and cherries.
Yields 32 (4 ounce) servings.
Ten recipes for 300 people.

title: super brownies
directions: Bake in jelly roll pan at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, nuts and melted oleo and pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
In bowl, beat 5 egg whites, 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar and water until stiff.
Add sugar and beat until stiff. Pour and spread evenly over crust.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Cool. Crush Heath bars and divide into 2 parts.
Whip 2 packages Dream Whip and fold in one part candy.
Spread over dessert.
Sprinkle remaining candy on top.
Chill 1 hour.

title: honey chicken wings
directions: Discard wing tips; cut wing into two parts.
Salt and pepper. Combine remaining ingredients.
Place wings into shallow casserole dish and cover with honey mixture sauce.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until sauce is caramelized.

title: hershey's kiss cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter with both sugars. Add egg, milk, vanilla, flour, baking soda and salt. Shape into balls and roll in white sugar. Put on ungreased pan and bake for 8 minutes at 375°. Remove from oven and press Hershey's Kiss into cookie until cookie cracks. Return to oven for 2 more minutes. Cool before handling.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 1-quart casserole.
In small bowl, beat egg yolks (reserve whites in small bowl).
Blend in milk, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Add sugar, flour and salt; beat until smooth.
Beat reserved egg whites until stiff.
Fold in yolk mixture gently but thoroughly.
Pour into prepared casserole. Place casserole in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour hot water into pan about 1-inch deep.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm or cool.
Garnish with whipped topping, if desired.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Stir cream cheese until very soft.
Gradually blend in 1/2 cup milk until smooth and creamy.
Add remaining milk and the pudding mix.
Beat slowly with eggbeater 1 minute.
(Do not overbeat.) Pour into cool graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top to make it extra crunchy.
Then chill.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and set aside.
Add sugar and vinegar to bacon drippings.
Separate the onion into rings and place in the skillet; add green beans.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
When ready to serve, crumble the bacon and sprinkle over the beans. Add almonds.

title: cheese filled bacon muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.

title: pork chow mein
directions: Slice pork, mushrooms, bok choy, water chestnuts, bamboo shoots and celery. Cut onion.
Mix cornstarch with water.

Heat the oil and salt in skillet with high heat for 1 minute. Add pork and stir-fry for 2 minutes. Add vegetables. Stir frequently over high heat 3 minutes. Add super soup stock or water. Cover the skillet and cook over medium heat 4 minutes. Add sugar, dry sherry and pepper.
Stir constantly. Add cornstarch-water mixture. Stir and turn around thoroughly. Serve with rice immediately.

title: onion-roasted potatoes
directions: In a large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Shake in the bag or toss in a bowl, until potatoes are evenly coated. Empty potatoes into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, powder and salt. Cut in butter. Stir in buttermilk and raisins to make a soft dough. Turn onto floured board and kneed 1-2 minutes until smooth. Shape a 6 1/2 inch diameter round and place on buttered baking sheet. Cut an x about 1/4 inch deep with a floured knife. Bake at 375 degrees for about 35-40 minutes until golden brown. Serve warm with butter and jam.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Crumble the cake into small pieces in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix thawed strawberries with the box of jello and pour over cake. Next mix the pudding and milk together, then add the ice cream to the pudding mixture.
Pour over strawberries.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate.

title: coconut mounds
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients together well.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill, then cut in long-like bars and dip in chocolate mixture of paraffin and chocolate chips or melt cubes of almond bark.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white until soft peaks are formed.
Slowly add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in pecans.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Place pecans about 1/2 inch apart.
Cook on 250 degrees for 30 minutes.
Cut oven off and leave for 30 minutes more.
Place in airtight container.

title: you're lucky if there's any left dessert
directions: Mix all together and press out smooth into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: popcorn balls
directions: In heavy saucepan, stir syrup, sugar and salt over medium heat.
Stir until boils.
Continue cooking, without stirring, for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour over popped corn.
Mix well and make balls.
It helps if you have butter on your hands.

title: catch-all casserole
directions: Crumble ground chuck on bottom of a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle salt, pepper and instant onions. Layer with potatoes, corn and beans.
Top with the soups. Cover loosely with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: best brownies ever
directions: Blend butter, cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Then add remaining dry ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana fruit cake
directions: Prepare 2 tube pans with Pam or Crisco and flour.
Chop fruit, leaving cherries and raisins whole.
Put fruit in dish pan.
Sift soda, salt, nutmeg and flour together.
Cream butter, add sugar and eggs (one at a time) and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Now add flour and beat until smooth.
Peel bananas and crush fine.
Pour into batter and beat well.
Turn batter over fruit with wooden spoon. Blend well.
Add buttermilk.
Put batter in tube pans.
Place in jelly roll pan with water.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Keep water in pan until done.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Cook macaroni.
Mix together ground chuck, macaroni, mushrooms, spaghetti sauce and 1 cup of cheese in 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese over top of casserole.
Bake 1/2 hour at 300° or microwave 15 minutes on High.

title: italian cream cake
directions: First separate egg yolks from egg whites.
Now, beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in coconut and chopped pecans. Lastly, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: spanish meatballs(diabetic recipe)
directions: Mix hamburger meat and seasoning mix into balls. Brown in skillet. Drain fat. Pour salsa over meat balls.

title: potato soup
directions: Pare and dice potatoes; add onion.
Cover with water and boil until soft, but not mushy.
Drain.
Add milk, parsley, salt and pepper to taste and butter.
Beat eggs.
Add some of the soup to it and pour mixture into pot.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix together flour, brown sugar, oatmeal and melted butter until crumbly.
Put 1/2 mixture into greased dish.
Add rhubarb, sugar, water and cornstarch.
Bring to a boil; add 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over rhubarb; add remainder of crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn dogs
directions: Heat cheese soup and milk together.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix ingredients for crust until crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup and put rest in pie plate like graham cracker crust.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a moderate oven (350°).
Watch crust closely so it doesn't get too brown.

title: rye bread mix
directions: Mix with mixer and serve with round rye.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; add flour.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Combine potatoes, margarine and spices.
Mix well.
Place in 1-quart casserole.
Top with Marshmallow Creme.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking soda together.
Add eggs and fruit cocktail with juice (should equal 2 cups).
Mix with spoon.
Pour into greased (not floured) oblong pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar.
Add pecans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Ice with coconut icing.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes and let cool.
Peel and cut in chunks.
Add sour cream with chives, Cheddar cheese soup, onion, salt and pepper. Mix well and pour into crock-pot; simmer for 2 hours (stir frequently).
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: holiday jelly
directions: Gather red corn cobs from barn.
Use 2 dozen cobs, well cleaned.
Cover with water and boil as you would fruit for jelly. Take 6 cups juice and place in pot.
Add 9 cups sugar and 1 box Sure-Jell.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 1 minute.
Pour into jars.
This tastes like a blend of apple and plum jelly.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: montego bay bars
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a square 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cook dates, granulated sugar, water and chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly about 10 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Cool.
Cream butter and brown sugar.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Press half the mixture evenly in bottom of pan. Spread with date mixture.
Top with remaining crumble mixture, pressing lightly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; then cut into bars.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix.
Combine salt, soda and flour.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add apples and nuts.

title: beef turnovers
directions: Cut through stack of roast beef, making 8 even sections.
Cut each pie crust into 4 sections.
Take 1 pie crust section and put one stack of beef in center (loosen beef).
Fold over and press edges with fork.
Make 3 slits on top.
Continue to make all 8 of them.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with gravy, broccoli and carrots.

title: swiss asparagus casserole
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter.
Saute asparagus.
Remove.
Put in a shallow baking dish.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons of butter until soft.
Stir in sour cream and grated cheese until cheese melts.
Pour over asparagus.
Top with crumbs.
Dot with butter. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: microwave chocolate oatrage snack cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate morsels.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer until creamy.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate morsels.
Spread batter into 8-inch square microwaveable dish; cover with waxed paper.
Microwave at High 4 minutes; rotate dish 1/4 turn.
Microwave at High an additional 4 to 5 minutes or until top appears dry.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate morsels over top of warm cake.
Let stand 10 minutes; spread over cake.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 12 squares.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a deep dish pie plate.
Place peaches on bottom.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and almond extract. Stir together dry ingredients.
Add egg and mix with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle dry mix over peaches.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix together cream cheese, oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well each time.
Sift 2 c. of flour with baking powder and gradually add to first mixture.
Flour the fruit and nuts with the remaining 1/4 c. and fold into batter.
Sprinkle bottom of pan with finely chopped nuts.
Bake in a well greased and floured pan at 300-325° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Start testing for doneness after the first hour.)
Use tube or Bundt pan.

title: monterey souffle
directions: Arrange bread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle over half the corn, half the chiles and 1 cup cheese.
Repeat.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Add everything, except drained pineapple, and mix well.
Then add pineapple.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.

title: hurry up chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, cocoa and salt.
Blend in oil and buttermilk.
Add eggs, mixing well.
Add boiling water, mixing well.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured cake pans. Bake for 35 minutes in 375° oven.

title: apricot bars
directions: Combine the flour, baking powder, brown sugar and oats; cut in butter.
Pat 2/3 of mixture into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread with preserves, mixed with water.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Arrange bread slices in an 8 x 11-inch greased baking dish (as many as it takes to fill it).
Cover bread with browned, drained sausage or ground ham.
Mix eggs, dry mustard and milk.
Pour over sausage.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top and cover with soup (undiluted).
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Bake, uncovered.)

title: salted peanut chews
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, butter and egg;
beat at low speed until crumbly.
Press in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 pan.
Bake for 12 to 18 minutes or until light golden brown.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle with marshmallows.
Return to oven; bake an additional 1 to 2 minutes or until marshmallows just begin to puff.
Cool while preparing topping.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all together cold and store in covered container in your refrigerator.
These will last for 4 months.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix shortening and flour. Add water. Let rest 10 minutes and roll out on floured surface.
Makes 1 pie crust.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients then add meat. Mix well. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Drain; let stand 5 minutes.

title: scotch cake
directions: Put all ingredients together and mix as pie dough.
Grease large size cookie sheet.
Roll between wax paper 1/2 of the dough and arrange in cookie sheet and up sides.
Add pie filling of your choice.
Roll second half
and put on top, sealing all sides. Beat whites from 1 egg and spread on top.
Add ground nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and 45 minutes at 300° (1 hour in all).

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus in a casserole dish; pour cream of mushroom soup over, then pimentos and then cheese.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Place in a 350° oven for about 25 minutes (or until cheese melts).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crisp fried cabbage
directions: Heat a frypan with a little oil.
Slice cabbage thinly into strips and fry a couple of handfuls at a time in the pan, adding more oil as cabbage absorbs it.
Turn over with a spatula to prevent burning and keep adding cabbage until all is used up.
Cook for about 5 minutes.
Be careful not to get it too oily.
Just before serving, sprinkle with sugar and soy sauce.
Turn once or twice.
Serves 4.

title: sausage rice stuffing casserole
directions: Cook sausage, celery, onion and mushrooms in large skillet until meat is browned; drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients and place in a greased 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(May be used to stuff a large turkey.)
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: baked stuffed chicken breast
directions: Prepare package of stuffing according to directions.
Stuff each breast cavity and close.
Wrap bacon around breast and secure with toothpick.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: easy lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine undiluted lemonade with Eagle Brand in a large bowl. When well mixed, add Cool Whip and mix well.
Spoon into 2 crusts. Store in freezer until shortly before serving.
*Can use frozen limeade.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Add buttermilk, then yeast mixture to dry mixture. Stir until thoroughly moistened, then knead in bowl a minute or two (no rising required).
Cut dough in half.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness on floured board.
Cut into rounds with cutter and dip in melted butter and fold over.
Bake 24 biscuits on greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Baked biscuits freeze nicely.
Also, dough may be refrigerated in plastic bag and kept.
Set out 1 hour before baking.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Grease pie plate. Beat ingredients in blender on high for 1 minute. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together; blend into creamed mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheets and press down with fork.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hot chocolate syrup
directions: In a saucepan, melt together the cocoa or chocolate squares and oleo; add sugar and Pet milk and bring to a boil.
Serve over cake and ice cream or a plain cake.

title: chicken salad special
directions: Combine chicken with celery, grapes, pineapple, walnuts, onion and salt.
Add mayonnaise and toss lightly until mixed.
Whip cream and fold gently into chicken mixture.
Chill thoroughly.

title: quick and easy german chocolate cake
directions: Combine all the ingredients and mix well. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Frost with pecan topping.

title: whole wheat pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Combine milk and oil; add to the flour mixture, stirring gently until flour sticks together.
Make into ball and roll until thin between two sheets of wax paper. Put into 9-inch pie plate and flute edges.
Fill and bake according to directions.
For baked shell, prick crust and bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 1 pastry shell.

title: marshmallow icing
directions: In a double boiler, mix egg whites, sugar, corn syrup, water, cream of tartar and salt.
Beat until it holds a peak.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and marshmallows.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour over remaining.
Stir and refrigerate 3 hours.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Cook and scramble sausage and onion together.
Put potatoes in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan (cake size).
Spread sausage and onion on top.
Pour 2 cans of soup on top.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple pie
directions: Brown the pie shell. Slice or dice apples. Mix the brown sugar over the apples. Put the apples in the pie shell. Mix by hand the sugar, flour, butter and cinnamon until it forms a powder. Spread over apples. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° until golden brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour cream and vanilla.
Mix well. Roll 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board or surface.
Cut with floured cookie cutters.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Ice with confectioners frosting or already prepared frosting in a can.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix together and fry on medium heat.

title: pork chop lula's scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters.
Combine the bread and cracker crumbs, salt, pepper and butter.
Sprinkle 1/3 of the buttered, seasoned crumbs in a well-greased, round (8 x 2-inch) baking dish.
Cover with a layer of oysters.
Repeat layers.
Add Worcestershire sauce to milk and pour over oysters.
Then sprinkle remaining crumbs over top of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix and add food coloring.
Pour in pie crust and chill.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with one jar pizza sauce.
Add noodles and sprinkle browned ground beef over noodles.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Pour remaining jar of sauce over and top with pepperoni and remaining cheese.
Cover and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place a layer of potatoes and half of the cheese (sliced) and half of the onion in oven casserole. Repeat the layer.
Add salt, pepper and milk.
Cover top with bacon.
Cover dish with aluminum foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°. Remove foil last 15 minutes.
Be sure bacon is cooked well done.

title: varenyky(pierogi's)
directions: Mix flour with salt in a deep bowl. Add egg and enough water to
make a medium soft dough.

Knead on a floured board until smooth. Don't overknead, otherwise dough will get tough. Divide dough into 2 parts. Cover and let stand 10 minutes. Cut dough into 2 to 2 1/2-inch rounds after dough is rolled out.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix by hand until dry and crumbly.
Pat into greased pan (9x13).
Use wet spatula to pack down tightly.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375 degrees until edges are nice and brown.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: lottie moore's apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 9-inch square cake pan.
Mix sugar, butter (melted), egg (beaten), flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add in the raw apples.
Then stir in the vanilla and walnuts.
Pour into cake pan and bake for 30 to 45 minutes until pick comes out clean.
Serve warm with homemade vanilla ice cream.

title: fresh apple pound cake(from 1975 edition)
directions: Grease and flour a 10 x 4-inch Bundt pan.
Thoroughly stir together the flour, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl of electric mixer, at medium speed, beat together the oil, sugar (granulated), eggs and vanilla until combined.
Gradually beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° until cake tester in center comes out clean, 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Place cake in pan on a wire rack to cool for 20 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli soup
directions: Heat broth, onion, and broccoli to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in potatoes until blended.
Stir in chicken, cheese and milk.

title: kim's lasagne(serves 12)
directions: Boil noodles in salted water until soft, then drain.
Brown ground beef and add garlic, tomato paste, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.
Prepare a 2 to 2 1/2-quart casserole dish by spraying with Pam or rubbing with butter.
Layer noodles in the bottom of the casserole dish.
Add Muenster cheese, meat combo, Monterey Jack and cottage cheese in layers.
Repeat until all ingredients are gone.
Ideally, the last layer should be some kind of cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: roasted mutton with noodles
directions: Marinate meat in soya sauce, vinegar, tomato sauce, sugar and garlic salt for 6 to 8 hours.
Roast in oil and keep aside.

title: hot mushroom sandwiches
directions: Combine mushrooms, butter, mayonnaise, ham, salt and pepper. Spread evenly on the four slices of bread.
Sprinkle each with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese is bubbly, about 10 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook in oven 45 minutes at 325° to 350° or until thick.
You can double for larger dish.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, oats, milk, catsup, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pat meat mixture on plastic wrap to an 8 x 12-inch rectangle.
Arrange cheese slices over meat, overlapping as necessary and leaving edges of meat uncovered.
Separate onion slices into rings and arrange over cheese slices.
Using plastic wrap to lift meat, roll up, starting with 8-inch side.
Seal edges well.
Place in microwave-safe loaf dish or shallow baking dish. Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 23 to 25 minutes or until center is no longer pink (150°), rotating dish once or twice.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and slice.
Makes about 10 servings, 225 calories each.

title: onion fritter rings
directions: Beat egg, water, shortening and lemon juice until frothy.
Mix in dry ingredients until well blended.
Dip onion rings; let excess batter drip off.
Fry in small amounts in about 1-inch of oil which has been heated to 375°.
Fry about 3 to 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Spread out in a single layer on cookie sheet.
Place in 325° oven to keep hot until remainder are cooked.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and half of buttermilk.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add remaining buttermilk.
Blend in melted butter and add vanilla.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.

title: instant spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Store mix in an airtight container.
To serve, place 3 to 4 teaspoons mix in a cup.
Add 1 cup boiling water and stir well.
Yield: about 25 servings.

title: sugar free apple pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Line pie plate with bottom crust; add apples. Pour juice mixture over apples, dot with margarine. Roll out remaining pastry to fit top of pie, cut slits or an apple shape in top, place over filling; seal and flute edges. Bake at 375 for 30 min. Increase oven to 400° bake 15-20 min or until apples are tender.

title: powdered cocoa
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spoon in hot water according to taste.

title: carrot raisin muffins
directions: A yeasted Cheddar cheese bread can be toasted for breakfast, sliced and filled with turkey or ham for lunch, and heated and served with pea soup for dinner.
It makes a great loaf to take to a hostess or to give as a holiday gift.

title: corny clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon.
Leave drippings in pan and saute onions.
Add bay leaf, broth, celery, potatoes, juice of clams and pepper.
Cook, covered, 15 to 20 minutes, until potatoes are done.
Add corn and clams.
Cook, covered, 5 minutes.
Add cream and heat.
Add bacon last.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spoon sausage, onion and pepper over cubed bread.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Pour over sausage and bread.
Bake uncovered until eggs are set (about 45 minutes) at 375°.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Add all of the ingredients together.
Add enough broth to make batter runny.
Pour in pan and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: puppy chow
directions: Place cereal in a large bowl.
Over low heat or in microwave, melt chocolate chips.
Stir in peanut butter and margarine until smooth.
Stir constantly (stovetop) or frequently (microwave).
Add vanilla.
Pour over cereal, stirring until all is coated.
Place cereal mix in covered plastic container or sealable bag.
Add sugar and shake until sugar is absorbed.
Spread on wax paper to dry.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat good and bake in crust until done.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Brush chicken with salad dressing.
Coat with remaining ingredients.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat ball stew
directions: Make ground beef into balls and cook.
In large pan, mix soup and broth.
Add potatoes, carrots, onions and meat balls.
Simmer approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Quick and good.

title: mango chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a simmer over medium heat. Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, until thick (approximately 1 hour), stirring occasionally. Pour chutney into sterilized jars and cover with paraffin or canning lids.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients except potato chips.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: icebox cake
directions: Crush wafers fine; add pecans, raisins and coconut.
Mix well. Add milk and mix well.
Place on wax paper and shape.
Keep in refrigerator.
Slice and serve.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Combine the soups, milk and soup mix. Pour half into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Sprinkle rice on top. Arrange chicken over rice. Pour remaining soup mixture over all. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until rice is tender and meat juices run clear.

title: hot dog creole
directions: Cut hot dogs into 1/2-inch pieces.
Heat oil in large skillet. Add hot dogs.
Cook and stir until pieces are brown.
Stir in tomato sauce, corn with liquid, chili powder, salt and onion. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown onions in some butter.
Brown hamburger.
Add chili powder and tomatoes and ketchup.
Cook until done.
Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Add all together in a long pan.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Put foil over pan and cook in oven for about 20 minutes.
Take out and put Mozzarella cheese on top and reheat until cheese has melted.

title: baked steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces and brown in skillet with small amount of oil.
Transfer steak to baking dish.
Mix water and soup together. Pour over steak; add mushrooms.
Bake at 400° for one hour or until meat is tender.
Great served with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Put berries in pastry-lined plate.
Mix the sugar, flour, spices and salt; scatter over the berries.
Dot pie with butter and then top with crust.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: cousin charlie's christmas caramel corn
directions: Place first 3 ingredients on a cookie sheet with edges.
In a heavy saucepan, combine next 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat to boiling, stirring often.
Continue, stirring occasionally, until mixture is golden brown (about 15 minutes).
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn mixture, stirring gently to coat.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes; stir.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Transfer to foil; cool thoroughly.
Break up.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: salad
directions: The night before, tear (do not cut) lettuces into small pieces and store in fridge in Ziploc packs.
Refrigerate cans of baby corn, artichokes and chestnuts.
Be sure to drain before adding to salad!
Grate cheeses and put in fridge.
Cut into bite-size pieces and marinate in fridge overnight the broccoli, cauliflower and mushrooms in Italian dressing.
Toss together and serve! Great for big parties.

title: beef and spinach minestrone
directions: Place beans in a large bowl; add water to cover 3-inches above beans.
Let stand at room temperature overnight (if using fresh beans).
Cook bacon in a large Dutch oven until crisp; remove bacon.
Crumble and set aside.
Add onions, carrot strips, celery and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Drain red beans and add to sauteed vegetable mixture along with crumbled bacon, 6 cups water, tomatoes and spices.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Stir in pasta; continue to simmer until beans and pasta are tender.
Set aside.
Combine ground chuck, bread crumbs, egg and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Mix well.
Shape meat mixture into balls and place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until browned.
Drain well.
Add meat balls to soup mixture; simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Stir in spinach and zucchini; simmer an additional 15 minutes until spinach wilts. Serve hot with a Parmesan cheese garnish.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine cream
cheese,	milk,
vanilla	and
sugar with mixer. Add fruit.
Freeze in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Allow to soften a little before serving.
Serves 9.

title: crock-pot potato soup
directions: Combine water and flour in a jar; shake until well mixed. In 5-quart crock-pot, combine all ingredients (except sour cream, cheese and evaporated milk). Cook on low 8 to 10 hours. During last hour of cooking, add milk, sour cream and cheese. Heat to melt; serve. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: green sherbet punch
directions: Combine ingredients in a 5 to 6-quart punch bowl.
A frozen ice ring may be added for additional cooling.

title: crispy peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter together. Remove from heat. Pour in sugar and Rice Krispies. Blend well. Chill in refrigerator for approximately 2 hours.
Roll in desired size balls.

title: welsh cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Blend well.
Stir in raisins, milk and egg.
Roll out on floured board or pat carefully to 1/4-inch thick.
Heat electric skillet at 325° to 350°.
Use no oil.

title: betcha can't eat just one biscuit
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine baking mix, club soda and sour cream in large bowl, mixing well.
Roll out dough and cut with biscuit cutter.
Melt butter in 15 x 10 x 1 inch baking pan.
Bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 2 to 3 dozen biscuits.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo. Saut onion and pepper. Add all other ingredients except cheese. Put in casserole dish and bake at 325° for 45 minutes. About 10 minutes before done, add cheese on top and finish cooking the 10 more minutes.

title: orange cheesecake
directions: Press graham cracker crust mixture into a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes; cool.
Drain mandarin oranges, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Combine mandarin oranges and Cointreau; stir gently.
Set aside, stirring occasionally.
Combine cream cheese, orange rind and flavorings in large mixing bowl; beat until fluffy and gradually add sugar, beating well after each addition.
Pour filling into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cheesecake is almost set.

title: walnut pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan (this is crumbly).
Stretch in place.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Pour into pastry-lined pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with orange slices, if desired.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 or 40 minutes or until done. Cool before putting on icing.

title: beef log
directions: Mix well.
Put in refrigerator, covered.
Mix every day for 3 days.
After the third day, shape into rolls, approximately 3-inches around.
Put on broiler pan (to catch the grease) in oven for 6 to 7 hours at 160°.
Also depends on how thick the rolls are as to how long to bake.
Slice and serve with Wheat Thins crackers.

title: sunny citrus snackin' squares
directions: In medium bowl, sprinkle Knox gelatine over pineapple juice. Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Stir in Sweet 'N Low and orange juice.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch square pan and chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen squares.
Each square equals 4 calories.

title: skillet supper
directions: Brown sausage, onion and pepper, pouring off fat as it collects.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover. Simmer, stirring often, until macaroni is tender.
Sour cream or cheese may be added before serving.

title: chili pecan roll
directions: Bring cheeses to room temperature; mix together until well blended.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into rolls 4-inches long and 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Chill 30 minutes. Roll each in chili powder and wrap in foil.
Chill until firm. Cut into slices 1/2-inch thick and serve on round crackers. Yields about 3 dozen canapes.

title: isy's old fashioned banana bread
directions: Mix in order. Bake in 300° oven for approximately 1 hour, until golden brown.

title: "perfectly chocolate" cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour two 9 inch round baking pans.
Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla; beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour in to pans.
Bake 30-35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans to wire racks.
Cool completely. Frost.

title: moose steak sauerbraten
directions: Brown meat in fat.
Take meat out.
Add water and gravy mix and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add remainder of ingredients, along with meat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: fruit 'n pudding delight
directions: Mix pudding per directions on box.

title: taco salad
directions: Shred lettuce and spread on large platter.
Mix taco seasoning, cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread this on top of lettuce.
Dice tomatoes and put on top of taco mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
Slice or chop olives.
Pour taco sauce over top and sprinkle olives to garnish.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in large pan over medium heat. Add onion and garlic and saute until translucent.
Add meat and cook until browned, stirring frequently.
Blend in tomato sauce, taco seasoning, chilies and olives.
Simmer about 10 minutes. Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer tortilla chips over the bottom.
Add all the meat mixture, then the Mozzarella cheese and the sour cream.
Top with another layer of chips. Bake until heated through, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake until it melts.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving with more tortilla chips.
Makes 2 (8-inch) square pans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in greased casserole.
Top with 1 1/2 cups corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter or margarine, mixed together.
Put on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, sugar and oleo together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.

title: macaroni swinny pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch pie pan.
Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In large skillet, brown ground beef with celery; drain.
Stir in prepared spaghetti sauce and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add cracker crumbs, nuts and coconut.
Stir in baking powder; add milk. Mix well.
Butter and flour 4 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: turnip greens
directions: Wash greens several times and drain.
Combine greens, water, salt in large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Drain greens, reserving 1 cup liquid; set aside.
Saute onion in butter or margarine in nonstick skillet. Add onion and allspice to drained greens.
Dissolve flour and sugar in vinegar; add to reserved 1 cup liquid.
Add mixture to greens. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thickened.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in deep casserole dish.
Bake at 350 until broccoli is tender.

title: easy onion soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water, add onions.
Cook until tender.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add milk, salmon, etc.
Pack in sprayed pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
On platter, decorate with sliced eggs in a cream sauce.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on box and bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.
Punch holes in cake before adding topping.
Spread pineapple on top of cake.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, cream of coconut and pour over cake.
Spread Cool Whip, then sprinkle coconut on top.
Refrigerate three days before serving.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container.
Use 1/4 cup to 1/3 cup of mixture to 1 cup hot water.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook
squash without salt until tender; drain and mash. Braise onion
and pepper in half of the butter.
Crush 24 Ritz crackers and
add
to
the
squash.	Add
onion
and pepper to square mixture.
Add
grated cheese and mix well.	Add seasonings and mix.
Add
cream
and mix.	Beat eggs well and add to mixture. Put
in
casserole	dish.
Mix
24 more crushed Ritz crackers with remaining butter (melted) and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake in a 300° oven for 50 minutes or until light brown.
This makes one large or 2 small casseroles.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly; mix wet ingredients including blueberries, then blend together.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Use large muffin tin, grease bottoms only and fill 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Makes about 10 muffins.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Makes approximately 6 dozen cookies.
Cook at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: knox blocks
directions: In large bowl, combine all gelatins; add boiling water and stir until dissolved. Pour into large shallow baking pan.
Chill until firm. Cut into squares.

title: souper burgers
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion in shortening; stir to separate meat.
Add remaining ingredients except buns.
Cook 5 minutes; stir now and then.
Serve on buns.
Garnish with onion and tomato slices.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: cheese stuffed shells
directions: Shred cheeses; beat eggs with fork and combine with cheeses. Add spices.
Mix well with hand.
Cook shells as directed.
Drain well on paper toweling.
Stuff shells.
Pour small amount of sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay shells on top.
Cover shells with rest of sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cut apples into 1/4 inch slices, place in a buttered baking dish.
Add cinnamon and water.
Mix together the sugar, flour and butter until crumbly.
Spread over apples and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: delicious sweet potatoes
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and spread in greased baking dish. Sprinkle pecans over top.
Mix the brown sugar, flour and margarine; sprinkle over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and marshmallows in a pot; bring to boil. Boil 7 minutes over medium heat.
Do not stir.
Pour over other ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly until all butter melts.
Place in greased pie pan.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken with orange sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine all other ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat stirring constantly until the mixture starts to boil.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes for boneless or 50 minutes for boned chicken.
Serve over rice.
This recipe also works great with pork chops.

title: molasses tea cakes
directions: Place
soda in coffee.
Mix together, roll out and cut. Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: grandma's yeast rolls
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar. Add eggs. Dissolve yeast in warm water. Alternate water with yeast and flour to mixture. Add flour until consistency of dough. Put dough in greased bowl. Cover and let rise. Knead dough for 1 minute. Roll dough into 3-inch balls and place on greased baking pan. Let rise until balls are 3 times bigger. Bake until golden brown at 450°. Brush with melted butter.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Butter or spray inside of shallow 2-quart baking dish.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chili
directions: Mix together; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add water as needed.

title: microwave candied sweet potatoes
directions: Drain sweet potatoes, reserving 1/4 cup of the syrup.
In 2-quart microwave-safe dish,
place brown sugar, butter, orange rind, cinnamon and reserved syrup.
Cook at High 4 minutes, until mixture is slightly thickened.
Add sweet potatoes, gently stirring to coat with glaze.
Cook at High 1 minute until heated through.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix the crackers, butter and sugar together. Save 3/4 cup for topping.
Cook together the rhubarb, sugar, cornstarch, water and jello.
Let cool. Spread on the cracker crust.
Combine the instant pudding, milk and ice cream.
Put on top of the rhubarb. Top with Cool Whip and marshmallows.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion and pepper in margarine until brown.
Add rice, consomme, bay leaf and shrimp.
Cook until rice is done.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift together cake flour and sugar.
Set aside.
Beat until foamy egg whites, salt and cream of tartar.
Beat until very stiff. Sprinkle 1 cup sugar over egg whites and beat well.
Add vanilla and almond.
Sprinkle flour mixture over egg whites in small amounts, folding in gently.
Pour into ungreased tube cake pan. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken breasts and beef
directions: Wrap pieces of chicken in dried beef.
Place in casserole. Mix sour cream, soup and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 200° for 4 hours.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Mix in melted margarine, milk, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into deep dish pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: petite cheesecake
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Add egg, lemon juice and vanilla and mix well.
Line small muffin tins with papers. Place one wafer in bottom of liner.
Fill 2/3 full with cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and top with cherry or blueberry pie filling.
Store in refrigerator.

title: green chile egg salad
directions: Mash eggs. Add chiles, mayo (to taste) and Tabasco (to taste). Mix well and serve with bread or bagels. Serves 6 to 10.

title: lemon krispie dessert
directions: Mix butter, sugar and 2 cups Rice Krispies.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or large pot, brown meat in oil. Remove meat with a slotted spoon and set aside. Saute onion, carrots and celery in drippings over medium heat until tender, about 5 minutes. Add mushrooms, garlic and thyme; cook and stir for 3 minutes. Add broth, water, barley, salt and pepper. Return meat to pan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until barley and meat are tender. Stir in parsley.

title: florentine stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to package.
Squeeze spinach to remove moisture.
Combine spinach, egg, Ricotta and Mozzarella cheeses, onion, garlic, salt and nutmeg.
Stir well to blend.
Stuff shells, using about 2 tablespoons each.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients to form dough. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: fish chowder
directions: Heat all ingredients, except shell fish.
When hot, add shell fish and heat.

title: cheese shrimpies
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and spread on English muffins.
Cut each half in quarters and keep frozen until ready to use.
Heat on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute garlic, onion, bell pepper and celery in oleo.
Add rice.
Over low heat, lightly brown the rice.
As rice is browning, dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 cup hot water.
After rice is lightly browned, add bouillon mixture, then add remaining 2 cups water.
After water is mostly cooked off, add mushrooms. Allow rice to finish cooking and season to taste.

title: caramel delight
directions: In a skillet, brown pecans, coconut and butter; set aside. Blend cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish crumble graham cracker crust.
After blending cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk, add Cool Whip.
Layer on top of crust with 1/2 of Cool Whip mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the pecans and coconut. Then pour 1/2 of the caramel topping on the crust.
Then repeat for other crust.
Keep refrigerated.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Cut ham in half.
Mix softened cream cheese, mustard, onion and Cheddar cheese.
Put small amount on end of ham and roll.
May put toothpick in for each one for easy pick-up.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Thaw
dough
overnight in refrigerator.
Line bottom of greased 9 x
13-inch
pan
with
pecans.
Tear 1 loaf of bread into pieces and
place on bottom of pan.
Melt butter in milk, then add
brown
sugar
and cinnamon.
Remove from burner; add dry pudding and stir until dissolved.
Pour over dough in pan. Tear second
loaf
into	pieces	and
place
on top and beside pieces in	pan.
Cover
the pan with greased waxed paper.	Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn onto a cookie sheet immediately.

title: nasi goreng
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Brown and set aside.
Saute next 3 ingredients and set aside.
Saute shrimp in oil for 3 minutes and set aside.
For final ingredients, melt butter.
Add curry, salt and pepper and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil, then add Minute rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Gently stir all ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cake mix cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix all together, then add 2 1/2 cups lukewarm water.
Mix good.
Let raise 1 hour.
Knead dough and roll like cinnamon rolls.
Spread 2 sticks margarine (soft) on dough.
Mix 1 cup brown sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon and sprinkle on buttered dough.
Roll like jelly roll and cut in 3/4-inch slices.
Let raise 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 450°
in a well-greased iron skillet for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix well the remaining ingredients and pour on top of cake.
Mix. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Cut in squares.

title: calico cabbage
directions: Blend together
in saucepan.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: venison chili
directions: In a large heavy skillet or Dutch oven, brown the meat with the onions, celery and green pepper.
Drain any grease.
Add the tomatoes, tomato sauce, mushrooms, dark and light kidney beans, pepperoni, chili seasonings, Tabasco, salt, pepper, cumin, cumin seed and chili powder.
Bring to a boil stirring occasionally. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: limemade-lemonade punch
directions: Mix all together.
Float sherbet on top.
You can add vodka or gin, if you want.

title: white chocolate cookies
directions: Add Crisco to white chocolate and melt in microwave.
Stir to blend well.
Spread peanut butter on crackers and, using tongs, roll in melted chocolate until well covered.
Place on waxed paper to harden.
(I roll mine twice to give them a thicker coating.) If chocolate starts to get too thick, put in the microwave to warm up and it will spread better.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Saute large chopped chunks of onions, celery and peppers, along with diced garlic in olive oil.
Add chopped tomatoes and juice. Saute a few more minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve red hots and sugar in saucepan of water over low heat.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Pour into a 2-gallon container, then add orange juice and lemonade.
Mix well and pour into a crock-pot or coffee maker to heat and serve.
This makes 2 gallons.

title: rump roast cooked in slow cooker
directions: Salt and pepper roast and place in slow cooker.
Mix onion soup mix, water and mushroom soup and pour over roast.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or on high for 6 to 8 hours or until ready to serve.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Mix well. Slowly stir in beet liquid, blend to a smooth mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly over medium heat until sauce is clear and thickened.
Add butter and beets. Keep warm 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: nikki koller's cocoa mix
directions: Stir. Seal in tin or plastic container.
Heat 3/4 cup water in microwave.
Pour over 1/3 cup mix.
Drop marshmallows to cover.

title: "good" cole slaw
directions: Mix slaw, noodles, almonds and sunflower seeds.
Mix sauce packet from noodles with oil, vinegar and Sweet 'N Low.
Combine both mixtures.

title: rosamarina fruit salad
directions: Add the first 6 ingredients to medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cook to custard consistency.
Cool about 20 minutes.
Cook the macaroni; drain.
Mix with custard sauce; set in refrigerator overnight.

title: baked french toast
directions: In large flat dish, combine eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla. Let bread soak in mixture 2 minutes. Turn and let soak until all custard is absorbed.

title: frikadeller(danish meat balls)
directions: Mix meats, onion, salt and pepper.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating.
Lastly, add milk.
Form into small balls and brown in butter.
A little hot water may be added while simmering until done.
Serve with brown gravy made from drippings.

title: caravan hot chocolate mix
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine chocolate drink mix powder, dry milk powder, coffee creamer powder and confectioners sugar. Mix well.
Transfer to plastic bags or airtight containers.
For each serving, combine 1/3 cup mix and 2/3 cup boiling water.
Mix well.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 9 quarts dry mix, enough for about 100 (1 cup) servings.

title: zippy carrots
directions: Combine ingredients in a baking dish; heat for 15 minutes at 300° or prepare in a pan on top of the stove.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Marinate overnight in a flat covered container in the refrigerator.
Bake in shallow baking dish covered for 1 hour at 350°.
Turn wings and bake an additional hour uncovered.
Enjoy!!

title: broccoli and noodles parmesan
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces.
Cook in covered saucepan over medium heat for 6 minutes; drain.
Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in soup and seasoning; mix well.
Add Swiss and Parmesan cheese, stirring until melted.
Stir in Ricotta cheese, broccoli and cooked noodles.
Pour into casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: gramma's egg custard
directions: Blend eggs, milk, sugar, salt, and vanilla well.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with berries.
Bake at 425 for 25-30 minutes.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a bowl, place graham cracker crumbs, butter and 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Blend well.
Reserve 2 tablespoons for garnish.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom and sides of a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Chill in freezer.
In mixer bowl, beat cream cheese and remaining sugar until smooth and light. Beat in eggs, vanilla and cornstarch.
Stir in sour cream.
Pour mixture into prepared crust; bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 200° and bake for 45 minutes.
Cool for 3 hours. Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Mix and beat butter, mustard, salt and vinegar together.
Add mashed yolks and mix well.
If mixture is dry, add enough mayonnaise to make creamy mixture.
Fill egg halves; sprinkle with paprika.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix egg, oil, salt and sugar with electric mixer.
Add milk and vinegar; mix.
Add flour and baking powder; mix well (batter will still be just a little lumpy).
Add cornmeal and mix just until mixed in well.
Do not beat for long (10 seconds or so).

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Except for the chocolate morsels, mix all ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes without chocolate morsels.
Pour into greased and lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: love's broiled shrimp(from bascom's)
directions: Marinate for 1 hour, then cook in shallow pan. Baste and turn over. Don't overcook.

title: corn pudding
directions: Stir flour, salt, sugar and butter into the corn.
Beat eggs and put into milk.
Stir into corn.
Put into baking dish (should be at least 2 1/2-inches deep).
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 450°.
Stir every 10 minutes while baking.
Use long prong kitchen fork.

title: herb rolls
directions: Put first four ingredients in a 9 inch pie pan.
Let melt. Cut biscuits in quarters.
Roll in butter mixture.
Arrange pieces so they are touching in the pan.
Bake at 425 degrees for 12 minutes.
Let stand for a few minutes to absorb the butter and herbs.

title: kathy's caramel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut crust ingredients together until texture of oatmeal.
Pat 3/4 of this mixture into a greased 9 X 13 pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
As crust is baking, make filling.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.
Slowly add water.
Boil 8 minutes.
Stir small amount into egg yolks and add to hot mixture.
Cook 4 minutes.
Pour into pie crust.

title: cheese blitz
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Roll flat with rolling pin.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and egg yolks.
Spread on bread and roll up in a jelly roll.
Roll in melted margarine, then in cinnamon and sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Do not store in a tight container.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease pie plate; beat all ingredients until smooth (1 minute if using mixer). Pour into pie plate. Bake 50 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain cooked broccoli.
Mix with other ingredients.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish (greased).
Sprinkle with crumbled cheese crackers.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given, adding grated carrots last.
Pour in a greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all good. Put in boiler and cook until it gets thick. Put strawberries in a graham cracker crust and pour the liquid over the strawberries. Let the liquid get cool first. Put in cooler and let stand 2 to 3 hours. A very fast dessert to make.

title: salad of gold
directions: Heat the juice and water to the boiling point.
Pour over the gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Cut one carrot at a time into the blender container.
Cover and run at high speed until finely chopped.
Empty into a measuring cup and continue to process until 2/3 cup is chopped.
Add to the gelatin.
Put the milk, vinegar and cheese into the container (any remaining carrot will not bother).
Cover and mix at low speed until smooth.
Add to the gelatin and carrot mixture.
Stir in the pineapple.
Pour into a greased mold.
Chill until firm.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Stir in eggs, oil and vanilla and mix well.
Put batter in three 9-inch baking pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cake cool thoroughly and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onions in boiling salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots; fold in zucchini and onions.
Combine stuffing mix and oleo.
Spread half stuffing mixture in a lightly buttered 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture over stuffing.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture over vegetables.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hunter's hot dish
