directions: Cook egg noodles until tender and drain.
Brown hamburger and pork together with onion and green pepper.
In a large casserole mix all the ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves a lot of people!

title: green tomato relish
directions: Chop tomatoes, celery, pepper, onions, cabbage and cucumbers all together; add 1/2 cup of salt and let stand 2 hours.
Drain off all excess liquid.
In large pot mix sugar, mustard seed, pepper and vinegar.
Heat and when sugar dissolves, add chopped vegetables.
Bring to slow boil and fill sterilized jars.
Chill before serving.
Makes 7 (1 pint) jars.

title: prune pound cake
directions: Allow to simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour or until darkens in color and thicker. Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Let the icing cool off the heat as the finished cake cools in the tube pan on a rack about 15 minutes. Turn the cake out onto a rack placed on a sheet of waxed paper. Slowly spoon the icing onto the warm cake. Allow the cake to cool completely before slicing.

title: fluffy green tea-mandarin mold
directions: Drain juice from mandarins and grapes.
Reserve juices; refrigerate fruits.
Combine juices with water to make 2 1/2 cups; bring to boil.
Pour over gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add lemon rind and tea bags.
Steep 5 minutes.
Press liquid from tea bags. Add lemon juice.
Tint with green food coloring (if desired). Refrigerate gelatin mixture until syrupy.
Beat until light and foamy.

title: strawberry-melon cooler
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in container of an electric blender.
Top with cover and process until smooth.
Stir in club soda.
Serve over ice.
Yields 4 cups.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a saucepan. Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Cut acorn squash in half.
Remove seeds from each piece. Place in shallow pan, cut side up.
Spread 1 heaping tablespoon margarine or butter in each half.
Add 2 heaping tablespoons brown sugar to each half.
Add 1 tablespoon Karo, if desired, for more sweetness to each.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: western hash casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add tomatoes, bell pepper, onion, rice, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Dredge chicken in milk and egg.
Mix and dip in flour. Pan-fry until slightly brown.
Arrange in casserole dish covered with half soup, sour cream and wine mixture.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Use rest of sauce at table.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat ingredients by hand.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost and serve.
Store in refrigerator.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Mix 1 can each lemonade, orange juice and grape juice with water as directed on the cans.
Pour each juice into an ice cube tray, setting aside any juice that is leftover.
Freeze.
About 15 minutes before serving, mix second can of lemonade and combine with ginger ale in a punch bowl or pitcher.
Add remaining reconstituted fruit juices and fruit ice cubes.
Makes 2 quarts or 12 to 14 servings.

title: pickled green beans
directions: Wash beans; cut in 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook beans, onion and celery in boiling water 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain well. Combine sugar, mustard seed, salt, turmeric, vinegar and water in large saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Add vegetables; simmer 5 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Cool well and refrigerate.

title: quick chicken 'n' dumplings
directions: You will also need a deep-dish casserole dish.

title: chicken seashell salad(serves 12 to 15 people)
directions: Simmer chicken breasts in salted water with onion until tender (about 1 1/2 hours).
Cool and cut into 1/2-inch squares. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add other ingredients.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. In separate bowl, mix applesauce and soda.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Add flour mixture alternately with applesauce.
Add raisins and bran.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie pan.
Bake at 370° for 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat two minutes at medium speed.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely on wire rack.

title: easy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spaghetti until near done; drain well and place in greased casserole dish.
In large mixing bowl combine chicken, soup, milk and mushrooms.
Pour over spaghetti. Sprinkle cheese over top of mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until cheese is melted and sauce is bubbly. Serves 8.

title: fudgy fondue
directions: *Use cake pieces, marshmallows, cherries, grapes and strawberries.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Boil peas and beans 2 minutes and drain; cool.
Cut cauliflower; wash and drain.
Mix mayonnaise and dressing mix. Pour over vegetables and mix.
Refrigerate.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat in large heavy pan. Add chopped onion and let cook until onion wilts.
Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain and add to meat.
Add all other ingredients. Cover and cook very slowly until cheese is melted.

title: "caviar" appetizer
directions: Drain first four ingredients.
Mix with creamy Italian dressing, chill overnight and serve with tortilla chips.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour the boiling water over the butter or margarine and the oatmeal.
Cover; let set for 20 minutes, stirring once.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Combine with oatmeal mixture; pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: pina colada pie(low fat - sugar free)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell(s).

title: strawberry bundt cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to eggs and butter mixture with milk alternately.
Bake at 350° on lowest rack in oven in greased and foiled Bundt pan for
1 1/4 hours, until well browned.
When cool, dust with 10x sugar.
Allow cake to cool in pan 15 minutes before removing.

title: bacon wrapped chestnuts
directions: Wrap a piece of uncooked bacon around each chestnut; secure with a toothpick.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until bacon is done.
Drain off the bacon fat.
Mix the brown sugar and ketchup in a bowl, then pour this mixture over the chestnuts.
Bake for another 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Do not brown meat.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: almost like k f c fried chicken
directions: Pour the oil into a pressure cooker and heat over medium heat about 400°.
In a small bowl, combine the egg and milk; in a separate bowl, combine the remaining dry ingredients.
Dip chicken pieces into the milk until fully moistened.
Roll the moistened chicken into the flour mixture until completely coated.
In groups of 4 or 5, drop coated chicken into the oil and lock lid in place. When steam begins shooting through the pressure release, set timer for 10 minutes.
After 10 minutes, release the pressure and remove the chicken to paper towels, or a metal rack to drain. Repeat with the remaining chicken.
Makes 12 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk until it begins to thicken.
Fold in Cool Whip and sour cream.
Layer, in a large dish, the pudding mix, bananas and wafers, repeating until all ingredients are gone.
Let chill for several hours before eating.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix wafers and oleo for crust.
Mix sugar, vanilla and cream cheese.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Spread on crust and add cherry pie filling.

title: grilled mexi burgers
directions: In a medium bowl, combine ground meat, taco seasoning, green chilies and onion.
Shape into 4 or 5 patties.
Grill or broil until done, turning often.
Serve on buns with taco sauce and favorite toppings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and cool. Combine butter and flour.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook slowly over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Pour over macaroni.
Mix well.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Add more milk, if desired.
Additional cheese may be spread on top of macaroni.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fingers(makes about 4 dozen small bars.)
directions: Cream butter. Gradually add sugars; cream well. Blend in egg, 1/3 cup peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla. Add flour and rolled oats; mix well. Spread in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned. Sprinkle immediately with morsels. Let stand 5 minutes

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, reserving the syrup.
Add water to pineapple syrup to make 1 cup. Combine gelatin, pineapple syrup, vinegar and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in pineapple, carrots and pecans.
Turn into 9x5x3 inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares to serve. Makes 8 servings.

title: old-fashioned peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Add peaches. Sprinkle with lemon juice and almond extract.
Pour into pastry-lined 9-inch pie pan; dot with butter.
Adjust top crust. Cut steam vents.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into loaf on broiler pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bar-b-que kraut
directions: Mix together kraut, sugar, tomatoes and fat in a 9 x 13 dish; crumble bacon over the top.
Bake at 325 degrees uncovered till dry, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: precooked biscuits
directions: Mix shortening into flour.
Add enough milk to make a workable dough.
Roll to approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Cook and bake at 400° until not sticky.
Biscuits can be kept in refrigerator for several weeks.
Reduce shortening to 6 tablespoons if you like a less flaky biscuit.
Can be frozen.

title: holiday cherry salad
directions: Mix and chill 4 to 6 hours before serving.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Combine in order given (mix well).
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake until filling is firm, about 30 minutes.

title: nutty sandwich
directions: Put the cream cheese in a bowl.
Let sit for about 1/2 hour. Add walnuts to the cheese.
Mix the cream cheese and walnuts. Spread on 4 slices of raisin bread.
Top with remaining 4 slices. Cut sandwiches in half.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix together well Miracle Whip, Parmesan cheese and oregano. Spoon over chicken in baking pan.
Bake about 45 minutes at 375° or until tender to fork.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix margarine and cheese in mixer.
Add flour and pepper.
Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir into flour
mixture.
Shape into little to medium balls. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut extra long slices of cheese into 3 equal portions (this makes 12 slices).
Pour melted butter over rye bread cubes; mix thoroughly.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Alternately place layers of zucchini, onion, tomato, pepper, cheese and bread cubes in casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Repeat process twice, ending with bread cubes.
Cover; bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour, or until vegetables are tender.
Serve hot. Makes 6 servings.

title: marinated beans
directions: Drain beans.
Place in bowl.
Next in small saucepan, heat together sugar, vinegar, oil and black pepper.
Pour over beans. Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Stir once or twice before serving.

title: bacon stuffed burgers
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and mix well.

Make 8 thin beef patties. Place an equal amount of mixture on 4 patties. Place remaining patties on top and pinch edges together. Grill or broil 6-inches from heat source, 6 or 8 minutes a side or as long as you prefer. Makes 4 burgers.

title: ambrosia pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10 inch tube or Bundt pan. In a large mixing bowl, combine the butter, shortening and sugar. Beat until well blended. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add the coconut extract and beat well. In medium bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, and salt.
Stir to mix.

Add to the batter alternately with the orange juice, starting and ending with the flour mixture. Stir in the coconut. Pour into the prepared pan and place pan in a COLD oven. Set the temperature to 325 degrees. Bake for 1 hour 25 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of cake. Turn out of pan immediately.

title: sweet and sour shrimp
directions: Mix together the vinegar and rice wine, slowly adding the sugar to taste and stirring constantly.
The mixture should have a sweet but sour taste.
Remove the shells from the shrimp; devein if you prefer.
Heat up oil in a pan.
Add shrimp or chicken when pan is hot; cook until done.
Reduce heat.
Pour vinegar mixture into pan; stir well.
Mix cornstarch and water; slowly pour into pan to thicken mixture.
Stir until bubbles (you may not need all of thickener).
Add green onions just before serving.
Serve with or over rice.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onions, green pepper, tomato, peas, celery, 9 slices bacon and Swiss cheese in a 9 x 11 x 2-inch dish.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: layer salad
directions: You will need 1 large container, dish or bowl with lid.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook mixture to a boil;
then add beets and cook for 15 minutes.
Pack in hot jars;
then pour syrup over the beets.

title: boysenberry or blackberry pie
directions: Roll out bottom crust and place in pie pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: midori cake
directions: Beat all ingredients 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool about 15 minutes in pan and then turn onto cooling rack.

title: inside out ravioli(serves about 10)
directions: Brown onion, garlic and beef (or turkey combination) in small amount oil in skillet (large).
Cook spinach using package directions.
Drain, reserving liquid and adding enough water to make 1 cup.
Add this liquid, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, tomato paste and salt to hamburg (meat) mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes. Combine spinach, macaroni, shredded cheese, bread crumbs, eggs and oil.
Spread in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with the meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until crisp-tender.
Cool.
Add onion and pepper rings.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over vegetables. Marinate for 12 hours or more.
Keep 3 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter in double boiler.
Put powdered sugar and cocoa in a large bowl.
Mix melted butter and cheese and pour into bowl of powdered sugar and cocoa.
Add vanilla.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: alice's maple fudge
directions: Melt block, being careful not to burn (melt slowly).
Add peanut butter; stir.
Add powdered sugar (enough to knead).
Add nuts.
Roll into logs or pour into pan.
Cut into slices or squares before it hardens.
Store in airtight bags or containers. Keeps a long time.

title: skillet meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix lightly.
Pour mixture into lightly greased ovenproof skillet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.
Contains 225 calories per serving.

title: shake and bake potatoes
directions: Dip potatoes in milk and coat with Shake 'n Bake.
Salt to taste.
Bake on cookie sheet with 1/8-inch cooking oil.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn 2 or 3 times.
Good with sour cream.

title: corn and tomato relish
directions: In a large pot, combine all ingredients except cornstarch and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir cornstarch and water until well blended.
Add to vegetables and stir until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes. Ladle mixture into hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath 15 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 pints.

title: party pickles
directions: Place cheese slice on ham slice.
Spread with cream cheese and roll around pickle spear.
Fasten with 3 to 4 toothpicks and cut into sections between each toothpick.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburg; drain.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add ground beef.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending after each addition. Mix together bananas, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to dough
mixture. Add nuts and mix.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: smothered steak roll-ups
directions: Cut steak into 6 pieces (about 8 x 4-inch).
Pound with meat hammer or edge of heavy saucer.
Place 1/4 cup stuffing near center of each piece of meat.
Roll-up, tuck in ends and fasten with skewers or toothpicks.
In skillet, brown roll-ups in shortening. Pour off fat.
Add soup and water.
Cover; cook over low heat 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix onion, celery, tomatoes and tomato paste together in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Cut steak into bite size pieces.
Add to sauce.
Reduce power setting to 50% power.
Cover casserole and cook 25 to 30 minutes, stirring 1/2 way through cooking time. Let rest for 10 minutes after cooking time.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Gradually add scalded milk. Add rice, raisins, vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Set in shallow pan.
Pour hot water in pan 1-inch deep.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: busy day cocoa frosting
directions: Add butter to boiling water.
Add vanilla.
Beat and when well blended, add sifted sugar and cocoa.
Beat until smooth and creamy (3 minutes), adding additional liquid, if necessary until of right consistency to spread.
Spread on warm cake.
This is a good inexpensive and quick chocolate frosting with good dark chocolate color.
It keeps well for several days without hardening.

title: april fool dessert
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Pour pudding into individual serving bowls.
When pudding begins to set, place peach half, rounded side up, in center of pudding.
April fool! You have a fried egg.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Stir in milk and vanilla; beat. Stir in flour, soda and salt; beat good.
Add nuts.
Chill for 1 hour and drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Blend together in mixer the first 5 ingredients.
Add well drained, crushed pineapple.
Pour into a baked graham cracker crust.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together in a casserole dish and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: marian's curry dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables. Makes about 2 cups.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, Karo syrup and water until small drop from spoon spins thread.
Add peanuts and stir continuously, cooking until mixture turns a brownish gold.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, salt and baking soda.
Mix. Pour onto buttered large cookie sheet.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt
butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cream-style corn, whole grain corn and corn bread mix.
Add beaten eggs and sour cream. Let
sit
10 minutes before baking in 350° oven for 30 minutes. May be topped with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine margarine, butter, cream cheese and sugar; beat well. Add salt and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour; mix well.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pickled beets
directions: Bring sugar, water, vinegar and lemon juice to a boil.
Add spices in a cloth bag and boil.
Add beets and cook 15 minutes. Put into hot jars and seal with hot lids and rings.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Unroll dough into 2 long rectangles.
Place in prepared pan.
Press over bottom and 1/2 inch up sides to form crust, sealing perforations (this is very important to seal).
Bake dough at 375° for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Make dressing (all ingredients except cheese and broccoli). Pour over flowerets and coat well.
Let set in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.

title: fiesta loaf
directions: Split bread lengthwise and pull out insides.
In large bowl or skillet, combine meat, bread, vegetables and soup.
Mix well. Stuff mixture into bottom half of bread shell.
Arrange cheese slice halves on top of mixture.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Put top on bread and slice.
Makes a good meal with beans and a salad.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, molasses and egg.
Add rest of ingredients.
Chill for an hour.
Roll into balls.
Roll each in granulated sugar.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender. Freeze.
Serve in sherbet dishes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: sausage and green bean casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together and then mix cooked sausage into ingredients; mix well.
Put in 9 x 13 casserole dish and top with a little grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You can mix this the night before and put in the refrigerator and bake the next day.
If you put it in the oven cold, it will take longer to cook.

title: red sauce
directions: Mix the sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir the water and fruit juice in gradually.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir in the almond flavoring and food coloring, if desired.
Use over cake slices or ice cream.

title: taco plate for two
directions: In a skillet, cook beef and onions over medium heat until meat is no longer pink.
Drain.
Stir in taco sauce, chilies and salt. Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 6 to 8 minutes or until heated through.
Spoon over chips.
Sprinkle with cheese Yield:
2 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute corn, onion and green peppers in 4 tablespoons of butter for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with the flour and mix well.
Slowly add milk.
Cook until thickened.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Add 1 cup cream and 2 tablespoons of butter just before serving.

title: peanut crisp bars
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup.
Cook and stir until dissolved. Remove from heat.
Blend in peanut butter, then stir in cereal. Spread in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt and add milk.
Cook over low heat.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens and boils. Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; stir a small amount of mixture into beaten egg yolk.
Return to hot mixture.
Cook one minute.
Add peanut butter.
Put in baked shell.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Put all ingredients into ice cream freezer.
Make as directed in freezer instructions.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans over bottom and set aside.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour over pecans and coconut.
In large bowl, mix cream cheese, oleo, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spoon on top of unbaked cake mix.
Do not spread.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Should test done in the middle.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan and cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Meanwhile, in another saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in the flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Drain potatoes and place in a serving bowl.
Add cream sauce and toss gently.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients; remove 1 cup.
Add buttermilk with soda.
Mix with dry ingredients; add egg and vanilla. Sprinkle the 1 cup of crumbs on top of cake after you put it in baking pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
If baking in a glass dish, use 325° oven.

title: brownies
directions: Blend vegetable oil, sugar and vanilla in a bowl.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Spread into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
Pour over corn flakes.
Mix and drop by spoon on waxed paper (buttered).
Allow to cool.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Roll in 1-inch balls and put in freezer until cool.
Take out of freezer and dip in Hershey bar which has been melted with the paraffin.
Put on wax paper.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Remove wrappers from caramels and combine with 1/3 cup milk; melt and stir.
Combine cake mix with remaining milk and butter. Mix dough until it holds together.
Stir in nuts.

title: italian sausage and peppers
directions: Cut sausage in bite size pieces.
Put into a large skillet with water and bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring once, until the sausage is no longer pink. Remove skillet from heat; strain off water and sausage fat.

title: white chili
directions: In large saucepan, combine water, lemon pepper seasoning and cumin seed.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear.
Remove chicken from bones.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Return chicken to saucepan.
Spray medium skillet with cooking spray.
Heat until hot.
Add garlic.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Add to chicken mixture.
Add onions to skillet.
Cook and stir until tender.
Add cooked onions, corn, chiles, cumin and lime juice to chicken mixture. Bring to a bowl.
Add beans.
Cook until thoroughly heated.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream cheese and butter together.
Add sifted flour that has been sifted 3 times with red pepper.
Add Rice Krispies.
Make into small balls the size of a nickel.
Flatten with fingers. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade chicken 'n noodles
directions: Cook chicken about 1 hour or until very tender.
Retain broth. In a large bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Add flour (1/2 cup at a time); it will make a stiff dough.
Using a lot of flour on your rolling pin and surface, roll until 1/8-inch thick or less.
Let set while you bone the chicken into bite size pieces.
Bring broth to a boil; add cubes and parsley.
Cut noodles into 1-inch strips and drop in.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken - easy bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread chicken pieces with sour cream, then roll them in cracker crumbs.
Melt butter in large Pyrex dish or jelly roll pan.
Lay chicken pieces 1 at a time in melted butter and immediately turn buttered side up.
Bake 1 hour; needs no turning.
Yields 6 servings.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Mix all.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: baked rice
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Bake in a 325° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package plus add 3 tablespoons creme de menthe.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan as directed on package. Cool.

title: taco salad
directions: Shred lettuce very fine.
Place in bottom of dish.
Cover with thick layer of chopped tomatoes.
Dump on beans (drain half juice off kidney, none off chili beans).
Cover with thick layer of cheese.
Pour dressing over; do not toss.
Cover with Fritos.
Beat when refrigerated 30 minutes to 1 hour (without Fritos).
Good with picante sauce.

title: louise's savory chicken
directions: Debone and skin chicken pieces.
Flour, salt, pepper and sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Brown in fat.
In an electric skillet, mix mushroom soup and milk until it makes a gravy.
Put in browned chicken.
Sprinkle with thyme.
Slice onions over the top.
Put lid on and cook slowly for 2 hours.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Boil 2 cups water.
Add Jell-O to dissolve.
Add rest of water, sugar, pineapple juice and bananas.
Then add Sprite and strawberries.
Put sherbet ice cream in mixture and let melt as you serve it.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage.
Add to tomato sauce.
Then add Ricotta cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Cook lasagna noodles, then drain.
Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put a little of sauce on the bottom of pan, then layer the noodles, sauce and cheese; do this 3 times.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and it is heated through.
Serve with garlic bread and a salad.

title: oops pie
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package instructions.
Pour half mixture into bowl and refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, pour remaining Jell-O into another bowl.
Fold in whipped topping (8 ounces).
Place this bowl in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Back to plain bowl of Jell-O.
Once Jell-O has set up somewhat, add in strawberries and pineapple.
Gently fold in remaining Cool Whip. Pour Jell-O fruit mixture into pie crust.
Once the other mixture has chilled for 15 minutes, remove from refrigerator and pour over 1st layer.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into balls, then roll in cinnamon; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lady baltimore cake(old recipe - over 50 years)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy.
Combine milk, water and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients and liquids alternately, in small amounts, beating well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry; fold into batter.

title: southern cornmeal muffins
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of the mixture. Combine egg whites, yogurt and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon mixture into muffin pans coated with spray.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove from pans immediately.
Makes 1 dozen; 1 muffin counts 1 bread, 1 fat and 25 optional calories.

title: everyone thinks it's crab dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts finely and mix all ingredients well. Place in small, ovenproof crock and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Must be heated through.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: cheesy chili for a crowd
directions: Brown meat with onion in 4-quart Dutch oven or saucepot on medium-high heat; drain.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, tomato paste, water, chili powder and cumin. Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Stir in process cheese until melted.
Spoon over macaroni.
Top with sour cream.
Makes 12 servings.
Prep time:
10 minutes.
Cooking time: 20 minutes.

title: imperialicious chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients except butter and chicken.
Dip each piece of chicken into melted butter, then into bread crumb mixture.
Be sure each piece is well coated.
Arrange in shallow roasting pan; pour any remaining butter over all and bake about an hour, until fork-tender, in 350° oven.
Turn if you wish or baste with drippings.
Makes four to six servings (or 2 to 3 if you live in my house!)

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend well.

title: wassail
directions: Stud 3 oranges with cloves.
Bake in pan with a small amount of water for 30 minutes at 325°.
Heat cider and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer uncovered 5 minutes.
Pour in punch bowl and add hot oranges.
Makes 40 cups.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into 4 to 6 pieces.
Dip steak in water and roll in Bisquick.
Brown in Crisco in a large skillet.
Salt and pepper steak while browning.
Chop green pepper and onion together in a small bowl.
Put browned steak and drippings in a large pan.
Put green pepper, onion, soup and water over meat.
Cover with foil. Cook in 375° oven about 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until fork-tender.

title: peloponnesian pot roast
directions: Make slits in top of roast with tip of knife; insert garlic cloves.
Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper.
In large skillet brown meat on both sides in hot oil.
Combine tomato sauce, vinegar, nutmeg, cloves, cinnamon and allspice.
Pour mixture over meat in skillet.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat to cutting board; keep warm.
Bring juices in skillet to boiling; boil, uncovered, about 5 minutes or until liquid is reduced to 3 cups.
Remove garlic cloves from meat, if desired.
Slice meat.
Spoon some of the sauce over the meat; serve remaining sauce with spaghetti.

title: frozen peach salad
directions: Mix all together in blender.
Pour in mold and freeze. (Can use bundt pan).
Turn onto platter of curly lettuce just before serving.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain juice from pears.
Heat juice to boiling point.
Pour over gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and cream until smooth.
Add gelatin and beat until blended. Chill to thicken.
Pour in drained, mashed pears and whipped cream.
Pour into mold.
Garnish with cherries.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and blueberries.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Stir in lemon juice.
Cool slightly.
Yields 2 cups sauce.
Serve over pancakes, ice cream, waffles, etc.

title: blueberry buttermilk muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt into a large bowl. Make well in the middle of flour mixture and add buttermilk, eggs and melted butter.
Mix gently.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon batter into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven 20 minutes or until done.
Serve muffins warm.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Place beans in a very large heavy kettle; add water, cover and soak overnight.
Next day, add onions, green pepper, celery, ham, sausage, salt, cayenne pepper and black pepper to the beans in their soaking water.
Bring to boiling over high heat, lower heat so that liquid ripples gently.

Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours. Uncover, stir well, turn heat to lowest point and cook, uncovered, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours longer, stirring now and then, until the beans are very soft and mixture is about the consistency of chili. Stir in onion tops and cook, uncovered 10 minutes, then mix in parsley and cook for 10 minutes more, stirring frequently.
Dish up the red beans and rice separately and put out big bowls so every one can help himself to as much rice as he wants.
Ladle the red beans on top.

title: cheddar baked potato slices
directions: In bowl, combine and mix soup and paprika.
Grease a 2-quart oblong dish.
Slice potatoes with skin on in 1/4-inch slices.
Pour soup over potatoes.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 10 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Test with fork.

title: st. patrick party punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, grapefruit juice, sugar and Kool-Aid in a gallon container.
Add enough water to fill container.

title: quick chicken
directions: Season chicken pieces with salt and pepper and garlic powder. Mix milk, soup and wine together.
Place chicken in baking pan. Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Garnish with paprika.

title: cracker salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl except for the 2 eggs.
Mix in enough salad dressing or mayonnaise to hold together.
Slice remaining 2 eggs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: saucy apple swirl
directions: Blend sugar and cinnamon.
Grease 10-inch Bundt pan and dust with about 1 tablespoon of sugar and cinnamon mix.
Blend cake mix, applesauce and eggs until moistened.
Beat as directed on package.
Pour about 1/2 batter in pan.
Sprinkle with remainder of sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Drizzle with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken sesame balls
directions: Combine chicken, onion, parsley, curry powder, mustard and paprika in a bowl. Add mayonnaise, 1 tablespoon at a time, blending thoroughly.
Make into balls using 1 teaspoon of the mixture. Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: vegetarian zucchini casserole
directions: Steam the zucchini and onion over boiling water for 2 to 3 minutes until just tender.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in greased pan for 35 minutes at 350°. Cut in small squares while warm, like brownies.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix molasses, boiling water and soda; pour into bottom of unbaked pie crust.
Blend flour, brown sugar and butter by rubbing together with hands.
Sprinkle lightly over molasses mixture. Bake in 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes or until crumbs are brown. Liquid will cook through crumbs, making a cake like texture. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix in bowl or blender.
Store in container with lid.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute ingredients except noodles. Add cooked noodles.
Put into buttered casserole and sprinkle one cup cheese over top and place in oven at 400° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Beat in the sugar, sour cream, vanilla and whipped topping. Pour into a graham cracker crust and refrigerate 4 to 5 hours until set. Top with your favorite fruit topping.

title: killer burrito casserole
directions: Brown ground meat; drain fat.
Add bell pepper, onion, salt, pepper, tomatoes and Velveeta cheese.
Simmer on low heat for 15 minutes.
Place flour tortillas, one at a time, in hot cooking oil for about 5 seconds.
Drain on a paper towel.
Put a small portion of the meat mixture on the bottom of a long casserole dish.
Add about 2 tablespoons of meat to each tortilla; roll up tortilla and place in the casserole dish.
Top with remaining meat mixture and Cheddar cheese; bake for 30 minutes.

title: nita's chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix together soups, tomato sauce and can of tomatoes in saucepan and heat.
Saute together onion, mushrooms and bell pepper.
Add to soup mix.
Mix together cooked spaghetti and deboned chicken and place in large casserole dish.
Pour into casserole the soup mixture and top with grated cheese and heat in oven at 350° until hot and bubbly and cheese has melted.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Cook and bone chicken; reserve 1 cup broth.
Combine soups and green chilies with chicken meat.
Add spices, peas and carrots with broth.
Preheat oven to 350°.

Cover bottom of 2 1/2 or 3 1/2-quart baking dish with corn chips, then alternate the combined mixture with cheese and chips in layers, ending with cheese. Sprinkle top with onion rings and bake 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: light hush puppies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Fry in deep oil (push off by teaspoon, one at a time).
These hush puppies will turn over in oil by themselves.

title: sue's cheese ball
directions: Mix and let stand for best taste.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill in the refrigerator overnight.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

title: moist date cake with buttermilk icing
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla, nuts and dates.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cool and spread with icing.

title: caramel dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.	Makes a delicious dip for apples.
Keep stored in refrigerator.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute ground beef and garlic in oil, then add next 5 items and simmer 20 minutes.
While simmering, cook noodles in boiling, salted water about 15 minutes; drain.
Now fill 3-quart casserole dish (buttered or sprayed with Pam) with alternate layers of noodles, cheese, tomato sauce, and Parmesan, ending with a layer of sauce and Parmesan.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Place half the macaroni in bottom of a large Pyrex dish.
Add half the corned beef and half the onion.
Add half the butter and half the soup mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with grated cheese, potato chips or bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: whipped cream-filled banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add mashed bananas and eggs; mix well.
Dissolve baking soda in boiling milk.
Add to butter and egg mixture, along with flour.
Pour batter into two 8 1/2-inch cake pans and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, until browned and center springs back when touched.

title: great spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
In medium bowl, stir together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions.
Cover.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Makes 3 cups. Serve with chips, crackers on pumpernickel bread.

title: peach of a pie
directions: Cook strawberries, 1/3 cup sugar, cornstarch and lemon juice until mixture thickens; add red food coloring.
Beat cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar, salt, vanilla and milk in mixer until soft and creamy.
Line baked pie shell bottom and sides with cream cheese mixture.
Place peach slices on top of cream cheese mixture.
Then add berries mixture last, after it has cooled.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut
meat into thin strips.
In
skillet,
brown
meat, mushrooms and onion in butter; season with	salt
and
pepper. Add broth (rinse can out with water and add).
Cover; simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Gradually blend
cup water into
2 tablespoons flour.	Slowly add to
meat.
Stir
until thickened. Slowly
blend
in
sour cream.
Serve over noodles (regular), chow mein, or mashed potatoes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: my mother's pumpkin pie(mrs. henry sauls)
directions: Peel
and
cook
pumpkin in water until tender (drain). Mix remaining
ingredients.
Pour into unbaked crust; cook at 375° until set, then 325° for about 1 hour.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and vanilla, cream until light and fluffy.
Add flour and walnuts; mix well.
Roll into 2 inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325 for 18-20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; salt and pepper to taste.
Drain well.
Place in bottom of square casserole dish.
Place vegetables on top.
Cream potatoes and spread on top of vegetables.
Top this with shredded sharp cheese.
Bake, uncovered, approximately 30 minutes or until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into 9-inch uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Layer in crock-pot.
Heat until hot in crock-pot, about 2 to 3 hours on low.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in microwave and heat for 2 minutes on High. Stir, then microwave 2 more minutes. Add baking soda and stir until color changes.
Spray paper grocery sack with Pam.
Add the popcorn.
Pour caramel mixture on popcorn. Fold bag and put in microwave.
Heat for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake.
Heat another 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake.
Heat for 45 minutes.
Pour in pan to cool, stirring occasionally.

title: overnight breakfast
directions: Beat eggs, milk, and salt together.
Layer in 9x13 inch greased baking dish:
bread, cooked sausage or bacon, cheese. Pour egg mixture over layers.
Refrigerate until next morning or bake right away at 350° for 35-40 minutes.
Serves 6 - 7.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Pat cookies onto pizza pan, bake and cool.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Put on top of cookie. Then add glaze.
Slice strawberries on top of glaze.
Chill and eat.

title: strawberry congealed jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add all other ingredients except Cool Whip.
Mix and pour into a 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole. Refrigerate an hour or until it starts to congeal.
Mix in Cool Whip and return to refrigerator.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Store in airtight container.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat 1 egg fluffy and when adding each egg, beat until fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand milk and milk; mix well.
Add sugar, vanilla flavoring and salt, mixing well.
Pour mixture into freezer container and fill with milk.
If you plan to add fruit after the ice cream has begun to freeze, leave out some of the milk.

title: beef pinwheels
directions: Cut beef into 8 rectangular pieces.
Combine 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder, onion powder, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper in a small bowl. Sprinkle evenly on both sides of beef. Set aside.

title: huli huli chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chicken.
Mix well to make marinade.
Marinate chicken for 24 hours.
Broil, turning once, about 30 minutes.
Brush with soy sauce if desired.

title: fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

title: cherry salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine gelatin and hot water.
Add pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Pour into an 8 x 10-inch glass dish. Chill until set.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mash ground chuck into bottom of an 11 x 13-inch pan or smaller.
Spread cream of chicken soup over meat.
Place Tater Tots on top of soup and meat mixture.
Place in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes until meat is cooked and Tater Tots are browned.

title: baked sweet potato chips
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Spray 2 baking sheets with cooking spray.
Thinly slice potatoes in a food processor or by hand, they should be no more than 1/8 inch thick.
Arrange slices on baking sheets so they don't overlap.
Brush with oil and sprinkle with salt.
Bake chips until they begin to lightly brown, about 15 minutes.
Cool on a rack and serve.
Serves 4. Points per serving 2.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Combine syrup and sugar and melt.
Add peanut butter and melt it, then stir in corn flakes.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: chitterlings
directions: Clean thoroughly.
Place in large pot and cover with water, 3 tablespoons salt and 2 red peppers.
Bring to a boil and boil 10 minutes.
Pour water off.
Put on fresh pot of water and repeat, adding 1/4 onion.
Pour water off.
Repeat, because the third time is the charm.
Cut in bite size pieces, roll in sour cream and put in brown bag with 2 cups flour, 3 tablespoons salt and 1 tablespoon black pepper.
Fry in hot oil.
Serve hot with hot pepper sauce or dip in table syrup.

title: filled fritters
directions: Combine flour, water, milk and egg (amounts may vary, should be thin).
Spoon into greased skillet and fry.
When browned, remove to plate and fill with filling; then roll.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy saucepan (2 1/2-quart).
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes at medium heat, stirring to prevent scorching. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: quiche
directions: Blend - Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: world's best chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and set aside.
In large bowl,
blend sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Set aside.
Scald milk over medium-high heat; remove from burner and slowly add cocoa mixture, whisking with a whip to blend.
Return cocoa mixture to burner and bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Mix a small amount of this chocolate mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Stir quickly to prevent lumps.
Add yolk mixture back to chocolate mixture and again, mix quickly.
Bring to a boil again over medium heat and cook until mixture becomes as thick as custard.
Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into pie shell.
Top with your favorite meringue.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, melt margarine over low heat. Stir in flour, salt, mustard and pepper until smooth. Remove from heat. Gradually stir in milk until smooth. Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat for about 10 minutes or until thickened. Remove from heat. Stir in 1 1/2 cups of cheese until melted. Turn macaroni into a greased 2-quart casserole. Pour cheese mixture over macaroni; mix well. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top of casserole. Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: ozark pie
directions: Combine egg, sugar, salt, baking powder and flour.
Beat well. Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into well-greased (butter) 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely. Fill crust with ice cream.
Crush and sprinkle Heath bars over the ice cream.
Freeze.
Set out 10 minutes before cutting. Serves 8.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage with knife.
Cut onions in rings.
Layer cabbage and onion.
In medium saucepan, bring vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and celery salt to a boil.
Remove from heat, add oil.
Stir to mix.
Pour over cabbage and onion.
Cover with Saran Wrap; immediately refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: "no bake" quick italian rum cake
directions: Slice biscuits in half longways.
Place biscuits on bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle with rum extract.
Cover with chocolate pudding.
Add another layer of biscuits; sprinkle with rum extract. Cover with vanilla pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip and garnish with colored sprinkles.
Refrigerate.

title: refrigerator potatoes
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes.
Boil.
Cook potatoes completely. Drain and put into large bowl with the other ingredients.
Beat with mixer until creamy.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Put into a casserole dish as much as you need; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, butter and evaporated milk in a glass casserole (3-quart size).
Microwave, uncovered, on Full power for 5 1/2 to 6 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir once or twice during cooking period.
Microwave, uncovered, on Full power 3 more minutes.
Stir mixture occasionally to prevent it from boiling over casserole.
Stir in marshmallow cream and beat about 30 seconds.
Stir in vanilla and mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Refrigerate until chilled.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: simple chicken italiano
directions: In a large skillet combine chicken and about 1/3 of the Italian dressing.
Saute until chicken starts to brown.
Add vegetables and remaining dressing.
Cover.
Simmer 7 to 9 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.
Serve over pasta and sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 5 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Melt the butter in a frying pan.
Break the bread into pieces and put in the same pan as the butter.
Mix together all the ingredients into the pan.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add grated cucumber and garlic salt. Blend together until mixed well.
(If thinner consistency is desired, milk can be added.)
Serve with potato chips.

title: skillet custard corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Melt butter in iron skillet or baking pan in oven.
Sift cornmeal, flour, soda, salt and sugar in mixing bowl.
Stir in 1 cup of milk, eggs and buttermilk.
Pour into skillet, then pour other cup of milk over mixture.
Do not stir. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, onion, celery, bouillon, garlic salt, cornbread crumbs, eggs, melted margarine, salt and pepper.
Put layer in greased 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole and add cheese.
Add remaining squash mixture.
Top with bacon bits.
Bake at 350° (325° if glass dish) for about 2 hours.
Should be cooked slowly until golden brown, but still moist, if cooked too fast, it will burn.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Whip Dream Whip as directed on package.
Combine confectioners sugar and softened cream cheese; then add to Dream Whip.
Spread evenly in two baked deep dish pie crusts.
Pour half of pie filling on each.
(Looks good if you use back of spoon and press pie filling down into cream cheese mixture.)
Yield:
2 pies.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Blend together 3 cups flour, sugar, salt, and yeast.
Add warm water, oil and milk and blend mixture.
Mixture will be soupy. Mix for 3 minutes at high speed.
Add remaining flour, mixing well.
Form into rolls and let rise and place margarine on rolls. Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Makes 30 rolls.

title: prune squares
directions: Pour
boiling
water
over
cut up prunes; set aside to cool. Mix
eggs,	oil
and
sugar
together well. Sift flour, salt, baking powder and spices; mix well.
Add prunes.
Put in 9	x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.	Frost with a cream cheese frosting and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: sweet and sour cucumbers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except onions and cucumbers.
Peel and cut onions in rings; put in 1 gallon jar.
Peel and slice cucumbers; add to onions with enough water to cover, approximately 8 cups; shake.
Can use in 2 or 3 hours.
The longer they sit the better.
Refrigerate.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in baking dish (9 x 9-inch).
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry ingredients and melted butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until tender.
Delicious and sweet; kids especially like!

title: yeast rolls
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt; add water, then yeast, flour and egg.
Mix well.
Let rise in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in a 400° oven.
You can roll dough and cut with a cutter or make in muffin pan in 3 small balls to make cloverleaf rolls.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed brie fish
directions: Whisk 2 eggs.
Add pinch of whole fennel and pinch of dill seed.
Lay both fish fillets in mixture for 5 minutes.
Remove fillets and cover with breadcrumbs.
Set fillets aside, uncooked. Set egg mixture aside.
Drain 1 can of Polar crabmeat; set aside. Melt 1/2 stick butter with juice from 1/4 well-squeezed lemon. Add crabmeat.
Bring mixture to a sizzle in frying pan.
Remove from heat and add Grey Poupon.
Slice Brie long and thin.
In baking dish (tight fit is necessary), layer 1 breaded fish fillet on bottom.
Layer crabmeat, butter and lemon saute undrained. Pepper to taste and squeeze 1/4 lemon to taste.
Layer remainder of egg mixture.
Layer sliced Brie.
Add 1 breaded fish fillet on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes, then broil about 5 minutes to a golden brown.

title: squash muffins
directions: Mix flour and dry ingredients.
Cream the squash, butter and egg together.
Add milk.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vegetable-macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Do the same with the peas.
Combine; gently toss.
Cover; refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: garden rice salad
directions: Cook rice as directed on package, omitting butter.
Cool. Toss with next 7 ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Before serving, garnish with peanuts.
(Can add chicken, ham or turkey, if desired.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal cookie mix
directions: Oatmeal Cookie Mix:
Mix first 6 ingredients in large bowl. Cut in shortening.
Add rolled oats.
Mix well.
Can be stored in cool place.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Mash strawberries in a 2-quart glass measure.
Stir in pectin, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until mixture reaches a full, rolling boil.
Stir in sugar; microwave, uncovered, on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until mixture boils hard for 1 full minute.
Skim off foam with spoon and pour into hot, sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Cover with metal lids and screw on band.
Let stand at room temperature until cool.
Store in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.

title: chicken divan
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan and layer with broccoli and chicken. Mix together the cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and poultry seasoning and pour over the chicken and broccoli. Spread over the top the bread crumbs, butter and Cheddar cheese crumbs.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: molded tuna salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix rest of ingredients and combine with jello.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves 4.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend Crisco into flour until mixture is grainy. Add salt, then add beaten egg, water and vinegar.
Mix dough by hand.
This makes three 9-inch shells.
Dough can be made and refrigerated in covered bowl.

title: slush
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and add water to make 2 gallons. Freeze
to a slush.
Ginger ale or 7-Up may be added at serving time, if desired.
Yield:
50 servings.

title: cheese salad - congealed
directions: Heat soup to boiling point; add gelatin and cream cheese until dissolved.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
When it begins to congeal, whip with electric beater.
Add vegetables and mayonnaise. Mix lightly with fork; set away to congeal.
Mold as desired.

title: sausage balls
directions: Roll in balls.
Bake and enjoy.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken fry
directions: Wash breasts and divide in halves like chops.
Mix garlic, grated onion, cumin, salt, pepper, chili, lemon and 1 Tbsp. ghee. Spread over halved breasts and place in well-buttered dish.
Cover with foil and bake in oven for a half hour at 350°F. Cool chicken breasts on wire rack.

title: slaw
directions: Add enough Miracle Whip to mix it up good, to your taste.

title: seasoned popcorn
directions: Place butter in microwave dish; cover and microwave on High for 45 seconds (until butter melts).
Stir in dry onion soup mix. Place popcorn in large serving bowl.
Pour butter mixture over popcorn.
Toss and serve.

title: ann's one pan banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease regular loaf pan.
Place all ingredients in pan and stir with fork until well blended.
Beat vigorously for 1 minute or more.
Place in oven.
Bake until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 65 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.
Run knife around sides to loosen.
Remove from pan.

title: microwave greek-style beef in pita
directions: Cut sliced beef into strips, 1 x 2-inches.
Combine oil, green pepper, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper in 8-inch microwave-safe baking dish.
Microwave at High 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Add beef strips, stirring to combine.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Place equal amount of meat mixture in each pita half.
Sprinkle with tomato and cheese.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cook in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares. Serve cold as appetizer.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Save out 1 cup grated cheese to sprinkle over top after all ingredients have been thoroughly mixed and poured into casserole dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: potato deluxe casserole
directions: Put all ingredients, except chips or corn flakes, in large bowl and mix. Add salt and pepper to taste. Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with crushed potato chips or corn flakes. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Place biscuits in pan as directed on package.
Use spoon and pat biscuits flat.
Spread sauce on each biscuit.
Place pepperoni and cheese on top.
Bake as directed or until lightly browned.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill well. Slice bananas and coat with lemon juice.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: hawaiian pudding
directions: Mix together and spread evenly in an 11 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut butter roast
directions: Stir cornstarch and peanut butter into tomatoes.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Cook in double boiler on medium heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: cajun barbecue sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, saute the onion and pepper in olive oil until tender. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Cool, covered, in refrigerator.

title: sand tarts
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into balls and bake.
Remove and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: cherries crunch
directions: Press in pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake until brown or 20 to 30 minutes.

title: savory chuck steaks(for the grill)
directions: Combine steak sauce, brown sugar, lime juice and red pepper (reserve 2 tablespoons marinade).
Place beef steaks in plastic bag and add remaining marinade, turning to coat.
Close bag securely and marinate for 10 minutes.
Pour off marinade.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cook
pasta
in
bag and cool.
To seasoning packet add oil and
mix well.
Mix crab meat, celery, olives, onions and hard-boiled egg.
To
this add your parsley, dill weed, thyme, Nature's Seasons, salt and pepper.
Toss with cool pasta, then add mayonnaise,
sour
cream
and
grated
cheese.
Mix
well. Chill and serve with crackers of your choice.

title: sour cream nut bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add vanilla.
Add salt to flour.
Add flour alternately with sour cream.
Mix well.
Grease and flour bottom of 5 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
When baked, loosen sides of pan (while still warm); remove and cool on rack. Freezes well.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chopping can be done in food processor. The longer it stands, the better it is.
Store refrigerated.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Let water, yeast and salt sit until foamy.
Add eggs, lard and flour.
Let rise twice.
Roll out and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and cut in 1 inch pieces.
Let rise again. Bake at 400° until lightly browned, about 15 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Flatten out crescent rolls on large baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and Italian dressing; mix together and spread on cooled crust.
Chop veggies and spread over cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Put under broiler until cheese melts.
Cut into squares.

title: meat loaf(diabetic and low cholesterol recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients well except V-8 juice.
Put in loaf pan and pour the V-8 juice over it. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sirloin special
directions: Slash fat edge of steaks at 1-inch intervals. In skillet, cook steaks in butter over medium heat to desired doneness (8 minutes for rare, 11 minutes for medium and 18 minutes for well done). Transfer to platter. Keep warm.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until drop turns brittle in cold water.
Pour slowly over.
Beat egg whites; add nuts and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Spoon onto buttered pan.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add water and bouillon cubes and bring to a boil.
Add noodles and bring back to a boil, then add garlic powder and broccoli.
Cook about 5 minutes and add milk, shredded cheese and pepper.
Cook and stir occasionally until cheese melts.

title: mac-n-cheese
directions: Cook macaroni just before tender and drain. Put back in boiler. Add milk, butter, cheese, soup and sour cream; mix well. Put in oblong baking dish. Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: pork-carne con chili
directions: Clean all seeds from peppers, as this is what makes too hot for many person's tastes.
Pour boiling water over the peppers and let set for 1 hour.
Have enough boiling water so that it will make a pint when it is put in the blender an hour later.

title: grandmother's gingerbread
directions: Beat sugar, Crisco and eggs until fluffy. Stir in molasses. Mix dry ingredients together; add in small amounts with buttermilk to the sugar, Crisco, eggs and molasses mixture. Blend well. Spread evenly in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until a pick in center comes out clean. Cool in pan.

title: toll house pie
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and sugars; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter; stir in morsels and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 325° oven 1 hour.
Serve warm with ice cream garnished with sliced, fresh strawberries.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix crackers and oleo and spread in loaf pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Mix pudding with milk.
Add vanilla ice cream.
Pour over crust.
Spread Cool Whip over all.
Sprinkle with Heath bars. Freeze.
Very good.
Can be made the day before serving.
It will keep in freezer for a month or more.
Great for unexpected guests!!!

title: pecan tassies
directions: Blend together the cream cheese, oleo and flour.
Shape into 2 dozen balls and place in ungreased tart pans.
Press dough to cover bottom and sides.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup chopped nuts into each shell.

title: chicken-bacon sandwiches
directions: Combine chicken, celery, eggs, salt, pepper, bacon and pickles; moisten with mayonnaise.
Trim crusts from bread.
Spread chicken mixture on white bread slices; add lettuce.
Top with whole wheat bread; press down lightly.
Cut sandwiches in half diagonally.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, sugar, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add beans and onions; toss well.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours or overnight, tossing occasionally.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 8 or 10 servings.

title: slick dumplings
directions: Mix together.
Roll out and cut in thin strips.

title: reese's pieces
directions: Mix the peanut butter, sugar and margarine.
Microwave until it mixes smoothly.
Pam a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pat mixture in pan. Melt chocolate chips.
Spread over mixture.
Cut into small squares, then let candy harden in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the sugar and cream cheese.
Add the peanut butter, vanilla and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into chocolate or graham cracker crust and freeze.
Remove from freezer about 30 minutes before serving.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oatmeal and buttermilk; mix well.
Cover and let stand for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°; line muffin cups.
Mix together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Combine oil, sugar and egg; mix.
Stir into oatmeal mixture.
Pour oatmeal mixture into flour, just to moisten.
Add apricots and nuts. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mixture to rub on hog
directions: This recipe can be doubled until you have enough "Rub" for what meat you have.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put sliced fresh peaches in buttered casserole.
Mix first 4 ingredients.
Spread over peaches. Combine sugar and cornstarch. Sprinkle on top of dough.
Pour 1 cup boiling water on cobbler. Bake 25 minutes at 425° in an 8 x 8 x 3-inch pan.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Make a white sauce with 3 tablespoons of margarine, 3 tablespoons flour and 2 cups of milk.
Salt and pepper to taste. Mix noodles, soup and white sauce together.
Add cheese, eggs and tuna; mix just to blend.
Bake in a large baking dish for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: big bertha smoked brisket
directions: Place brisket on four (crisscrossed) sheets of heavy-duty tinfoil.
Liberally season with salts and cover with chopped onion.
Pour liquid smoke over entire brisket.
Wrap up in foil and refrigerate overnight.
Before cooking, pour off the liquid smoke and douse with Worcestershire.
Cover back up in foil and bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Uncover, pour some of the barbecue sauce over the brisket and bake 1 more hour.
Remove from oven and let sit 15 to 30 minutes before slicing.
Serve sliced with your favorite barbecue sauce.
Leftovers can be chopped for barbecue sandwiches.

title: shrimp and broccoli fettuccine
directions: Cook pasta for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix meat, bread crumbs, salt, eggs, onions and parsley.
Form into meatballs.
Brown in margarine.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Add preserves and barbecue sauce.
Mix well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make sheet cake as per directions on box.
Pour coffee over cake and allow to stand overnight.
Add milk to pudding mix as per instructions on the box.
Crumble half the cake in a deep dish. Pour one package of the mixed pudding over crumbled cake.
Spread one container Cool Whip over the pudding mix.
Repeat process, making 2 layers.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Put the sliced apples in the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Combine the flour, oats, brown sugar and cinnamon. Cut in the margarine until crumbly and sprinkle over the apples. Microwave on High for 14 to 16 minutes or until apples are tender. Serve warm.

title: tuna noodle casserole(microwave)
directions: Prepare pasta conventionally as package directs.
Drain; set aside.
In a 2 quart casserole, cook onion covered, at High 3 to 4 minutes until tender-crisp.
Stir in sour cream, milk, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add noodles, tuna, and vegetables; toss to mix well.
Cover.
Microwave at High 8 to 10 minutes until mixture is hot, stirring occasionally.
Let stand covered, 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese flavored cracker crumbs if desired.
Serves 6.

title: red potato and onion bake
directions: Cut potatoes and onions into wedges.
In large roasting pan, toss potatoes and onions in remaining ingredients until well coated.
Roast at 425° for 45 minutes, turning them once or twice, until golden or fork-tender.
Serves 6.

title: peach blueberry pie
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Combine peaches and blueberries.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, mace, salt, lemon peel and juice; add to fruits.
Toss with fork and pour into pie pan, heaping slightly in center.
Dot with margarine.
Cut 10 strips about 11 inches long and 1/2 inch wide.
Arrange lattice fashion over fruit.
Trim and flute edges.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Sprinkle breasts with salt and coat with mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator and coat with bread crumbs.
Place in single layer in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: salad dressing
directions: Note:
Burning the batch even slightly ruins the entire thing. Start over.
If a child is attempting this, a double boiler is recommended.

title: man on moon cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil until foamy.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon together and add to egg mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove from oven and spread with topping.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in the Crisco with pastry blender or two knives, until mixture has small lumps.
Add water gradually until the dough clings together so that the bowl is clean.
Chill dough.
Use 2/3 of the dough, roll out on a slightly floured board, keeping the dough as nearly round as possible.
Use this for the lower crust with remaining dough for top crust.
This amount makes enough for one 9-inch two-crust pie.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter each biscuit and roll in a mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.	Place in a Bundt cake pan (greased and floured).
Add nuts as you put in biscuits.
Bring to a boil butter or margarine, sugar and cinnamon.
Boil for about 1 minute. Pour over biscuits.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes; turn upside down on plate.
Serve warm for breakfast.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts. Beat eggs lightly in large bowl. Add sugar, oil and vanilla. Beat until creamy. Stir in zucchini and pineapple. Add dry ingredients, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened. Spoon batter into a 15 x 10-inch pan. Bake at 375°
until done.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in the order listed in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layers will just cover ingredients under them.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Top with sliced cheese.
Bake just long enough to melt cheese.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Add dry ingredients, then nuts. Bake in greased loaf pan for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple-cheese salad
directions: Cut your favorite apples in slices or chunks.
Cut the cheese of your choice in chunks.
Toss with dressing.
Sprinkle slivered almonds on top.
Peanuts are good, too.
A time saver, quick and easy, too.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt butter or oleo and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, gradually, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens, then cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Place over hot water to keep warm and cover tightly to prevent film from forming.
Makes about 1 cup of sauce.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup in a heavy boiler.
Bring to a boil and cook until mixture spins a thread.
Pour half of the syrup mixture over the egg whites and begin stirring.
Cook remaining half until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Pour this into the egg-syrup mixture.
Add vanilla and continue to stir until it holds its shape.
Add pecans and drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.

title: country casserole
directions: Combine in a large bowl. Place in a pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches. Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Uncover. Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: garlic steak
directions: Rip meat in pieces.
In frying pan, cook until brown.
Pour in garlic.
Pour in tenderizer.
Drain oil.
Cook for 1 minute.
Eat.

title: eda meissner's congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple; add gelatine to juice and allow to soften. Add sugar to drained pineapple and bring to boil.
Add hot pineapple to gelatine.
Mix and stir well; cool.
Add nuts and cheese.
Fold in whipped cream.
Grease 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish with mayonnaise.
Pour salad and chill well until congealed.
May add 2 tablespoons chopped maraschino cherries for color.

title: sweet cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed and pour into a greased 8 or 9-inch pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: batter bread
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder in a bowl.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Melt shortening in an 8-inch square pan.
Add half of melted shortening to batter.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine; saute onions until clear.
Add 2 tablespoons flour to small amount of the 4 cups of milk.
Mix with butter and onion.
Add the rest of the milk, a little at a time, whisking between additions.
Add Velveeta, broccoli and broth.
Add pepper to taste.
Heat until hot.
Serves 6.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix the cucumbers, bell pepper, onion and salt and cover; refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat egg and milk together.
Mix with other ingredients.
Top with crumbled saltines.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Wash beans.
Cover beans with water.
Soak beans overnight. Put beans and water into crock-pot.
Pour all ingredients into crock-pot and cook for 6 hours, until tender.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli spears as directed on package; drain and cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Melt margarine in a small skillet. Saute onions and celery for 3 minutes.
Place broccoli in the bottom of 1 1/2-quart buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle onion and celery mixture over broccoli.
Combine mushroom soup, sour cream and chopped pimento, spoon over vegetables.
Melt margarine, saute bread crumbs until margarine is absorbed.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raisin stuffed apples
directions: Core apples; pare strip from center or top of each.
Mix brown sugar and raisins.
Place about 2 tablespoons of raisin mixture in center of each apple.
Dot with butter.
Place apples in large saucepan; add water.
Cover tightly.
Bring to boil.
Continue boiling gently 15 minutes or until tender.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 servings.
Omit butter if serving apples chilled.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Combine the remaining ingredients and mix with broccoli. Turn into casserole and cover with crackers. Bake 45 minutes at 350.

title: chevrie cheese cake(goat cheese)
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter and spread in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Add gelatine to cold water. When softened, heat until gelatine is dissolved.
Add sugar, Chevrie cheese and vanilla.
Mix well (I use a blender).
Pour over crumbs and refrigerate.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; put in casserole dish.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: coventry cheese ball
directions: In a bowl, blend cream cheese, parsley and Cheddar cheese. Add onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt; blend well.
Shape into ball.
Chill and serve with crackers.
Quick and easy.
Tastes good.

title: pudding flan
directions: In a heavy cast-iron pan, heat 1 cup sugar with cold water, stirring constantly so that the sugar melts and caramelizes, but does not burn.
Pour melted sugar directly into the baking dish, quickly coating all inside surfaces of the dish.
Sugar will harden to candy consistency.
Set aside.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt candy bar (s) in microwave.
(Save enough of solid bar for garnish.)
Mix into Cool Whip and pour into crust.
Garnish top by shaving chocolate bar.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: sweet and sour dip
directions: Beat all ingredients well with mixer.
Great with veggies or chips.

title: scripture cake
directions: Preheat Leviticus 2:4 (oven) to 300°.
Heavily grease and flour verse 5 (two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans or 10-inch tube or Bundt pan).
In large bowl with electric mixer set at medium speed, beat softened butter with sugar.
Lower speed and add honey.
Add eggs one at a time.
In a large bowl, combine 3 1/4 cups flour, 3 teaspoons baking powder and 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Now add spices, mixing well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to batter.
Using remaining 1/2 cup flour, raisins, figs and almonds, mix these, then fold gently into batter.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until a cake tester comes out clean. Allow to cool in pan 30 minutes, then turn out onto plate to cool completely.

title: fresh peach or strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick and glossy.
Take off heat and add 1/4 cup of peach or apricot jello.
Let get cold. Add 2 heaping cups of peaches or strawberries.
Refrigerate and serve with Cool Whip.
Use strawberry jello for strawberry pie.

title: cranberry tea
