directions: Heat sugar and red hots in water until red hots melt.
Add undiluted juices.
To serve hot:
Dilute mixture with water half and half.
To serve cold:
Dilute mixture with 7-Up half and half.

title: christopher's snack bus
directions: Spread frosting on graham cracker.
Place 3 square crackers on for windows.
Place 2 round crackers on for wheels.
Place M&M's on for lights.

title: shrimp louis dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover; chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix together.
Put into graham cracker crust and refrigerate until firm.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, egg, ketchup and bread crumbs.
Roll until 1-inch thick between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Remove top sheet of waxed paper.
Saute onions, green pepper and mushrooms in butter or margarine.
Add salt, pepper and oregano.
Pour this mixture onto rolled out beef.
Roll up carefully.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour tomato sauce over it and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Put onion in blender.
Add salt, Mazola oil and vinegar. Blend together sugar and horseradish mustard.
Stir in poppy seed.

title: easy squash casserole
directions: Amounts of squash, etc. according to size casserole needed. If crackers are salty, salt not usually needed.

title: barbecued country style ribs
directions: Put ribs in roasting pan and roast at 425° for 30 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Continue roasting at 350° until tender. Spoon the sauce over the meat a few times.

title: aunt barbara's sour milk cake
directions: Cream together brown sugar and oleo.
Sift cocoa together with flour.
Alternately stir into the creamed mixture the dry (cocoa) ingredients and one pint sour milk.
Mix 1/2 cup hot water and 3 teaspoons baking soda.
Add to other ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup raisins.
Bake in large 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add zucchini.
Stir to combine.
Add oil and beat smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 13-inch loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: crispy cheese wafers
directions: Mix cheese and butter until smooth.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add rice cereal.
Roll into small balls, using a teaspoon for a measure.
Flatten with finger.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: 8 calorie chocolate kisses(the wonderful taste of chocolate with no cholesterol or fat.)
directions: Beat egg whites in a small bowl at high speed until foamy; add cream of tartar and beat until egg whites hold stiff peaks when beaters are lifted from mixture.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
When all sugar has been added and mixture holds stiff peaks but is still glossy, gently fold in sifted cocoa, 1 tablespoons at a time.
(Do not beat meringue after stiff peaks are formed.) Spoon kisses by scant teaspoon, 1 inch apart, onto an ungreased nonstick baking sheet.
Bake in a preheated 275° oven for 20 minutes or until kisses are "dry" to touch.
Cool on pan before removing.
When completely cool, store in a dry, airtight cookie tin.
Yields 9 dozen.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix together remaining ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Spread this combined mixture into a greased jelly roll pan (11 x 15-inch).
Bake at 400° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Crust should be light brown like a homemade chocolate chip cookie.

title: candied fruit cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt. Beat butter and sugar in bowl at medium speed until light and fluffy. Beat in egg at low speed; beat in buttermilk. Stir in raisins and candied fruit. Chill 1 hour. Grease baking sheets. Drop dough by tablespoon 2 inches apart on sheet; flatten slightly. Bake in preheated 375° oven 8 to 10 minutes.

title: amber's brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a pan.
Put in oven and bake at 500° for 100 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spread hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt one stick of margarine and pour over potatoes.
In separate bowl, mix cheese, onion, salt, pepper, sour cream and soup.
Spread mixture over potatoes.
Melt remaining margarine and pour over dish. Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ruby's apple-walnut drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Lightly grease several cookie sheets. Sift flour with baking soda. Mix shortening, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and eggs until well blended; stir in flour mixture. Drop by rounded tablespoonful of dough onto cookie sheets about 2-inches apart. Bake 11 to 14 minutes or until done. While cookies are still soft, spread thinly with glaze. Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen.

title: chicken cutlets
directions: Place cutlets in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Grate the Swiss cheese over chicken.
Mix the soup and sherry or white wine.
Sprinkle the stuffing mix over all.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Serve with rice or noodles and a vegetable (or vegetable casserole).

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make ahead, at least overnight.
Keeps for days.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables with soup.
Put in baking dish.
Place cheese slices on top of mixture.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over cheese.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook mixture until it reaches a rolling boil.
Cook 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla. Beat and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: kabobs
directions: Using toothpicks, skewer Cheddar cheese, sweet gherkin and ham.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream Crisco, oleo and sugar together.
Beat egg yolks and add to creamed mixture.

Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add alternately with flour to which a pinch of salt has been added. Add coconut and pecans and fold in beaten egg whites and vanilla. Bake in 9-inch cake pans for 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: kentucky supreme cake
directions: Blend in order.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Add pecans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: two minute microwave fudge
directions: Stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and flavoring together in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl until partially blended.
Put butter on top in center.
Microwave at High for 2 minutes or until milk feels warm on bottom of dish.
Stir vigorously until smooth.
If all butter has not melted in cooking, it will as mixture is stirred.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Mix all together except nuts. Make a ball. Roll in nuts.

title: hungarian sausage loaf
directions: Combine sausage, bread crumbs, beaten egg and sour cream. Season with paprika.
Pack in loaf pan firmly.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours. Serves 6.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix all sauces together.
Add sugar, several dashes of garlic salt, onion salt and oregano.
Cook macaroni.
Cook hamburg and onion, salt and pepper.
Mix macaroni, hamburg and tomato mixture. Pat 1/2 mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese and pepperoni.
Add rest of mixture and top with cheese, pepperoni and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: potato stuff
directions: Mix together, cover with cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for one hour in a 9 x 12-inch dish.

title: easy ambrosia
directions: Combine fruit in serving bowl; sprinkle with pecan halves (optional).
Spoon frozen orange juice over top; let stand until orange juice thaws.
Stir fruit gently; top with cherries.
Yield: variable.

title: rigatoni with sausage, peppers and eggs(prep: 10 minutes, cook: 20 minutes, serves 4)
directions: Brown sausage meat in a large skillet, stirring and breaking up pieces with the side of a fork; drain off excess fat.
Add the peppers, onions, mushrooms and garlic.
Cook, covered, over low heat until the peppers are tender and the onion begins to turn golden, about 15 minutes.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix in a large bowl and place in 8 x 10-inch casserole dish. Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream dill dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, parsley, minced onion and dill to make dip.
Use hollowed bread for bowl and bread cubes to dip.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add sauce and simmer.
Mix eggs with cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Layer sauce on bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next layer cheese mixture, next Mozzarella cheese, then noodles, sprinkle a little water over noodles.
Alternate until all of the ingredients are used up. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Make a tent of aluminum foil over the pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until done at 350°. Cool 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: dry russian tea mix
directions: Put 3 teaspoons of mixture into a cup.
Add boiling water.

title: fresh cranberry relish
directions: Wash cranberries, oranges and apples.
Cut apples into eighths.
Cut unpeeled orange into eighths, remove seeds.
Place half of berries and oranges in food processor.
Process until mixture is evenly chopped.
Transfer to bowl.
Repeat with remaining fruit.
Stir in sugar to desired sweetness.
Frozen berries need less sugar.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes 3 cups.

title: honey-thyme mustard spread
directions: Stir ingredients together in a small mixing bowl.

title: california chicken(made with tuna fish)
directions: Boil carrots and onions together for 15 minutes.
Add potatoes; boil until tender.
Season.
Cream flour and butter; add milk.
Cook in a double boiler for 15 minutes.
Add peas to other vegetables.
Drain water from tuna fish and break up, then add to sauce.
Place layers of vegetables and white sauce alternately in baking dish and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken stew
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour rice into a baking dish.
Place vegetables on top of rice.
Put cut-up chicken parts on top of vegetables and rice.
Salt and pepper.
Add 4 cups water.
Cover with lid or aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Good with plain white rice, too.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat softened cream cheese.
Add eggs and sugar; blend.
Add vanilla and sour cream; beat.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Turn off oven.
Leave pie in oven 50 minutes.
After removing pie from oven, pour 1 can or jar of prepared cherry pie filling over cheese cake pie.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and pepper together.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend sugar and eggs together.
Mix syrup into mixture.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until center is firm.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Melt margarine.
Add crumbs.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat powdered sugar and cream cheese together.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread over crumbs.
Spread pie filling on top and refrigerate.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in an iron skillet at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: In saucepan boil 1 cup stock.
Put dried mushrooms in bowl and pour boiling stock over.
Soak 1 hour.
Meanwhile boil another cup of stock.
Add barley, cover and simmer gently until barley is somewhat tender, approximately 25 minutes.
Melt butter in soup pot.
Add onion and cook to soften, about 4 minutes.
Add celery, carrots and parsnip.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soy sauce and cook until most of it has evaporated, 2 minutes.
Add remaining stock, barley, fresh mushrooms, wine, tomato paste, dill, bay leaves, basil, thyme and oregano.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer gently for 1 hour. Shortly before soup is done, drain dried mushrooms, reserving the liquid.
Cut into pieces and add to soup.
Strain liquid from dried mushrooms and add as well.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. This soup can be refrigerated for several days.
Thin with additional broth or water as necessary.

title: walnut hummus with cilantro
directions: In a blender, using 3 tablespoons garbanzo bean juice, mix all ingredients into a smooth paste; chill.
Don't be afraid to use lots of seasoning because the beans are bland.
Serve as a dip.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Melt 1/3 cup margarine.
In small bowl, combine crumbs, sugar and melted margarine.
Press on bottom and side of 9-inch pie plate; set aside.

title: chicken and dressing bake
directions: Mix chicken and soups. Place in baking dish and spread stuffing mix on top.
Melt oleo and pour on top. Add the chicken broth and bake at 375° until bubbles up well all over.

title: garlic bread
directions: In a cup, stir sprinkles into the water until dissolved.
Stir in Parmesan, oregano and garlic.
With a pastry brush, lightly coat both sides of each bread slice with mixture.
Form bread back into a loaf and place on sheet of aluminum foil. Wrap well. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Marinate chicken in a mixture of the remaining ingredients. Place chicken in marinade in broiler pan 4-inches from the heat for 5 minutes.
Turn chicken, broil 5 more minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: homemade egg substitute
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients. Mix well.
Use as a substitute for 1 egg.

title: pasta with italian sausage sauce(low in fat)
directions: Wash kale and tear leaves off stems and into bite size pieces. Crumble sausage from casings into large nonstick skillet.
Stir over medium heat 3 minutes, until browned.
Remove with slotted spoon to a plate.
Add kale to skillet; toss for about 45 seconds until bright green.
Stir flour into broth.
Add kale.
Bring to boil.
Add tomatoes to skillet.
Drain beans and add with crushed pepper.
Add sausage.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Add to hot pasta.

title: pig cake
directions: Beat cake mix, juice or water and vanilla for 4 minutes, then add oranges and beat until mixed.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Spray Pam in casserole dish and spread ingredients in order listed in pan with mushroom soup on top.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour until bubbly.

title: chicken parmesana
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken into egg and then bread crumbs, coating thoroughly.
In a skillet, heat the oil; cook chicken until done and well browned on both sides.
Pour sauce into an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on sauce and top with Parmesan cheese and shredded Mozzarella.
Bake for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Marinate chicken wings.
Bake in 350° oven, turning about every 15 minutes.
Bake for one hour.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Mix together peas, soup and pimento in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Spread grated cheese on top of pea mixture.
Sprinkle onion rings on top of cheese.
Melt margarine and mix with Ritz crumbs and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: turkey divan casserole
directions: Spread broccoli in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch ungreased baking dish.
Drizzle with lemon juice.
Top with turkey and cheese slices.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over turkey and cheese.
Cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with onion rings and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: flourless peanut butter cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Roll level tablespoons into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° for about 18 minutes.
Remove to a wire rack to cool.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine first
4 ingredients and cook on Full power for 4 minutes, stirring twice.
Remove from microwave and add soda and vanilla.
Place
popped corn in large grocery bag or bowl. Pour caramel
mixture
over
corn,
shake
and
stir
to coat. Microwave 1
minutes
on High, shake bag or bowl well and turn it
every
30	seconds.
Pour out and let cool.
Easy and delicious.

title: five hour stew
directions: Place in covered casserole and bake in a 250° oven for 5 hours.
If you are a potato lover, you may add potatoes to stew after 3 hours.

title: pan-fish with marjoram and lemon butter
directions: Melt the butter in a skillet and add the garlic and marjoram. Add the fish which has been floured, salted and peppered.
Fry until browned on both sides (about 5 minutes on each side).
Add lemon juice, cover and cook over medium heat for another 10 minutes.
Pour lemon butter from the pan over the fish before serving.

title: jamaican salsa
directions: Put onions in strainer over a bowl (green and red pepper also). Pour 1 quart boiling water over them and let them sit in the water, while you prepare other ingredients. Then combine and mix thoroughly. Cover tightly and chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a large cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch dish. Cut bread into 1-inch slices and remove crust.
Arrange in a single layer in dish. Beat eggs, milk, salt, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: meat balls in tomato gravy
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Make balls (size of large lemons) and brown in hot oil.
Place in baking dish.
In another skillet, put 2 to 3 tablespoons oil.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons flour to make a paste.
Add 2 tablespoons yellow mustard and the rest of the soup.
Add water to make a gravy.
Pour over meat balls and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel pear and grind.
Combine pears, sugar and lemon juice in large saucepan.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is thick and clear, stirring often.
Add pineapple.
Mix thoroughly. Cook for 10 minutes more.
Pack in hot jars and seal.
Makes 12 pints.

title: olive nut sandwiches
directions: Mix the above ingredients to a spreading consistency.
Add a dash of pepper.
No salt is needed.

title: crock-pot beef and noodles
directions: Mix soups and water in crock-pot.
Add beef and cook several hours.
Cook noodles separately and add to crock-pot 1 hour before serving.

title: santa fe soup
directions: Mix; heat and serve with cornbread.

title: creole salad
directions: Combine the pasta, tomato, cheese, mayonnaise, olives, onion, garlic and cayenne pepper.
Chill thoroughly before serving (30 minutes to 1 hour).

title: broccoli salad from lynn
directions: Fry bacon, then crumble into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients in large salad bowl.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: granger cookies
directions: Roll large as walnuts.
Bake at 325° for 13 minutes.

title: oriental beef with vegetables
directions: Cook beef and onion in wok or large skillet over medium heat until beef is no longer pink, stirring to separate beef.
Spoon off fat.
Add garlic; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add vegetables; stir-fry 2 minutes or until heated through.
Add stir-fry sauce; stir-fry 30 seconds or until hot.
Serve over chow mein noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creole okra
directions: Cook onion, bell pepper and okra in 3 tablespoons bacon drippings. Stew corn if hard. Combine all ingredients and cook. Sprinkle crumbs with cayenne. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients; mix shortening in until it is of a consistency of coarse meal.
Add milk gradually, mixing with fork, to a soft dough.
Roll on floured board or waxed paper 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into squares.
Place apple (or peach) in center of dough square.
Apples having been washed, peeled and cored.
Fill center with sugar and small pat of butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bring up 4 corners of dough; press together firmly.
Place on greased pan and sprinkle lightly with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 minutes or until nicely browned.
Use sugar and spice according to taste, more or less.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: venison salami
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Cover and refrigerate 4 days.
Mix well each day.
On 4th day form into long rolls and bake at 225 degrees for 4 hours.

title: layered angel food cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin according to package directions.
Let thicken until almost set.

title: rice-sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Add green pepper, onion and celery and saute.
Combine soup mix in boiling water in large saucepan.
Stir in uncooked rice.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Add sausage mixture and salt.
Mix most of almonds with saving a few to pat on top.
Pour into greased baking dish, 12 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Boil sliced carrots in salted water just until tender; drain. Put carrots, sliced pepper and onion in layers in a large casserole.
Make sauce with remaining ingredients in boiler; pour over vegetables.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar with shortening until fluffy.
Mix in persimmon pulp, nuts and raisins.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and spices together.
Add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Bake as bar or drop cookies on parchment-lined cookie sheets at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: steak continental-style
directions: Mash garlic and salt together, then add next 5 ingredients. Score steak 1/4 inch deep on both sides.
Rub in garlic mixture. Wrap steak in waxed paper and chill overnight.
Grill over charcoal to desired doneness.

title: cherry surprise balls
directions: Yields 5 dozen cookies.
With electric mixer, cream butter and confectioners sugar until light and fluffy.
Remove beaters and stir in flour and vanilla.
When well mixed, stir in pecans.
Wrap dough in waxed paper.
Chill for several hours so it will be quite stiff.
Pinch off small portions of dough.
Flatten and roll around cherry to make a ball.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Bake about 20 minutes in a 375° preheated oven.
While still warm, roll in sifted confectioners sugar.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 13 x 9 inch pan.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 each of meat mixture, chips and the cheese in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes.
Top with lettuce and tomato, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken cheddar rice bake
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Blend in flour and chicken bouillon cubes.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken and mushrooms.
Arrange rice in greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Spoon chicken mixture over rice. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate logs
directions: Thoroughly mix the sugar, coconut, pecans, vanilla extract and graham cracker crumbs into the peanut butter.
Pour melted butter over the mixture and blend well.
Shape dough into 2 x 1/2-inch logs.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook squash.
Combine all ingredients except half of cheese and paprika.
Put into buttered casserole.
Cover with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortenings and sugar, then beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° in greased and floured (Pam may be substituted) tube pan or 2 loaf pans.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, corn meal and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Pour into the pie shells and bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until firm.

title: english toffee
directions: Measure all ingredients, except chips.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Over medium heat, melt butter.
Add sugar and water slowly. Stir constantly until mixture turns tan.
(Hard ball stage.)
The lighter the mixture, the softer the candy.
Pour on cookie sheet. Spread chips over immediately.
Sprinkle nuts over mixture.
Cool. Break into pieces.
(Tastes like a Heath Bar.)

title: blueberry bombe
directions: In a bowl, fold together the whipped topping, yogurt and pie filling.
Spoon into sherbet glasses.
Chill.
Garnish as desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Fold in 9 ounce Cool Whip.
Pour into baked 9-inch graham cracker pie shell.

title: potato soup
directions: Pour water, chicken stock or bouillon in a large heavy pot. Add potatoes, onion, celery, carrots and ham.
Cook until it comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Turn down heat so the soup simmers for 45 minutes.
If too thin, add a tablespoon of flour to the condensed milk before you stir it in.
Add the milk, parsley and chives.
Stir until hot and potatoes and carrots are tender. Serve.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and let set until almost jelled, not firm.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Let set overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cut in small pieces.
Cook 1 cup rice.
Mix the two soups with milk.
Add rice and chicken to the soup and milk mixture.
Mix well.
Put in a casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers to cover casserole.
Melt 1/2 to 1 stick butter; pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp remoulade dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except shrimp in food processor.
Stir in whole shrimp and serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix eggs, milk, sugar, pumpkin, spices and salt.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle cake mix over pie mixture.
Sprinkle pecans next.
Pour melted oleo over the whole pan on top of all the mixture.
Bake an hour or until cake mix is done at 350°.

title: shrimp scramble
directions: In medium bowl with fork, beat eggs and milk slightly.
Stir in shrimp, salt, pepper and mustard.
Meanwhile, toast English muffins.
Spread with butter; keep warm.
In an 8-inch skillet over medium heat, melt 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.
Add egg mixture and cook, stirring once or twice with fork, until eggs are set.
Spoon over muffin halves.

title: pork toutierre
directions: *You may use 2 pounds of ground pork instead.

title: maque choux(smothered corn)
directions: Saute onions in bacon grease until transparent, about 5 minutes.
Add corn and cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes and green pepper; cook 5 minutes or until very soft.
May be served as is or stuffed into cooked bell pepper or tomato and browned in oven.

title: skillet chicken stew
directions: Wipe pieces of chicken with paper toweling; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat the olive oil in large skillet with a tight-fitting lid.
Brown chicken on all sides in the oil.
Remove the chicken and set aside.
Add the onion to the oil and cook until it is glazed and transparent.
Add the rice as it comes from the package.
Add the basil, oregano and tomatoes; stir in the bouillon and sugar.
Last, add the chicken broth.
Turn heat down to simmer.
Cover and cook at simmer for 30 minutes.
Then turn each piece of chicken over and cook for another 30 minutes or until the chicken is tender and the rice is fluffy.
Leave the cover off in the last 5 minutes of cooking to let any liquid left in the bottom of pan evaporate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: red rice
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onions and bell pepper.
Add tomato paste and water.
Bring to boil.
Add rice.
Boil for a couple of minutes.
Lower fire and cook until done, stirring occasionally.

title: taco bean dip recipe
directions: Brown ground beef on medium heat and drain off excess fat. Add seasoning, taco sauce and refried beans.
Stir well (add a couple of tablespoons of water if too dry).
Cook for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place half of mixture in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with half of cheese.
Repeat meat and cheese.
Then microwave on High until cheese begins to melt (2 to 3 minutes normally).
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: hot cheese and crab hors d'oeuvres
directions: Blend together first 5 ingredients.
Stir in crabmeat.
Spread on English muffin quarters.
Freeze 30 minutes.
Bake or broil in 500° oven or until brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: krema sauce(for eggplant casserole)
directions: Over medium flame, brown flour with butter lightly for about 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally to avoid scorching.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
When it begins to bubble, remove immediately from flame.
Beat eggs well for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add to mixture along with cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Season to taste.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Make into balls the size of a cookie with thumb.
Fill thumb impressions with preserves, jam, jelly or cherry (red or green).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Soften the cream cheese. Add remaining ingredients to cream cheese.
Mix well and shape into ball. Sprinkle with salt and roll in more chopped pecans.

title: tatala(sponge cookies)
directions: Beat all together.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.
Before baking, sprinkle each cookie lightly with sugar.
Before serving, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender (about 10 minutes).
Stir in parsley and other seasonings.
In a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese; stir in vegetable mixture.
Separate dough in 8 triangles; place in an ungreased 11-inch quiche pan or 10-inch pie pan. Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture evenly over crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: witch's brew
directions: Combine punch and ginger ale.
Add pineapple, orange slices and cherries.
Refrigerate.
Real good!

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water in small saucepan. Cover tightly, heat over medium heat until mixture boils vigorously.
Uncover, boil rapidly, without stirring, to 242° on candy thermometer (or until small amount spins a 6 to 8-inch thread when dropped from a spoon).

title: chocolate-peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into one-inch balls.
Dip in melted chocolate.
(Dipping chocolate can be purchased at most large food stores or bake shops.)

title: mexican salsa
directions: Chop onion, garlic and peppers very finely.
They can be put through the blender or food processor with the cilantro.
Add the tomatoes and lemon juice; mash with a fork for a chunky salsa. Use more or less tomato juice for a dipping consistency.

title: glazed carrots and pineapple(microwave)
directions: Put carrots into an 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Mix reserved pineapple juice, brown sugar and salt.
Pour over carrots. Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook 5 minutes on High.
Add pineapple to carrots; mix well.
Cook covered 10 to 15 minutes on High.
Stir 3 times.
Mix cold water and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir into carrot mixture.
Cook uncovered 3 minutes at High.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ham and corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: cucumber pickle
directions: Soak cucumbers in
water
and lime for 24 hours.
Rinse and soak in clear
water
hours.
Put in vinegar, sugar and salt. Put in
bag celery seed, cloves and pickle spices.	Let cucumbers stand in
this overnight.
Next morning, cook for 30 minutes and can.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and milk to boil.
Stir 5 minutes over medium heat.
Take off heat.
Add marshmallows, vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: Melt the butter in 2 skillets.
Mix eggs and milk; salt and pepper to taste.
Scramble eggs.

title: angel food cake(diabetic)
directions: Slice cake in half.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Spread in between cake layers and on top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: crowd pleasing potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on, about 23 minutes, with bay leaves and salt.
Grate coarsely; set aside.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean and remove stems and slice a thin slice off the bottom of cap.
Chop stems and saute in butter.
Add the bread crumbs, cooking sherry, basil, parsley, walnuts and cheese.
Stuff mushroom caps and bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until mushrooms are soft.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll into balls and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar or colored sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 or 11 minutes.
Watch because they burn easily.

title: frozen pineapple pie
directions: Beat together Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add pineapple, Cool Whip topping and 1 cup of pecans.
Mix well.
This will fill the 2 graham cracker crusts.
Freeze.
Set out shortly before serving time and allow to soften enough to cut.
May be returned to the freezer.
Yield:
2 (8-inch) pies.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Mix together vinegar and sugar.
Drain dill pickles and slice thin, then add sugar and vinegar mixture.
Put back in jar. Refrigerate.
Stir next 2 or 3 days.

title: choco-peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat brown sugar, peanut butter and margarine until fluffy.
Blend in water, egg (or substitute) and vanilla.
Add combined oats, flour and baking soda; mix well. Cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Using bottom of glass dipped in sugar, press into 1/4-inch thick circles.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Remove to wire rack; cool completely. Melt chocolate pieces as package directs.
Stir in shortening, mixing until smooth.
Top each cookie with 1/2 teaspoon melted chocolate; sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Chill until set.
Store, tightly covered.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Saute garlic in margarine in a small saucepan until tender. Stir in cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Add milk, stirring well. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 2 minutes or until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Remove sauce from heat and set aside.

title: corn salad
directions: In a large salad bowl combine all vegetables.
Stir in dressing and refrigerate until serving.

title: complete meal casserole
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch pan, pat down ground beef.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread soup over next, then whole kernel corn, then French fried onions.
Arrange Tater Tots on top so that it is completely covered.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix all in mixing bowl.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until firm.
(Can bake in large utility dish.)
While cake is baking, mix juice of 2 lemons with 2 cups of powdered sugar.
When cake is done, punch holes with a meat fork or a large tined fork all over the cake and pour on the glaze.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Flatten chicken to 1/4 inch thickness.
Combine crumbs and 1 tsp. of mustard.
In a separate bowl, combine honey and remaining mustard.
Dip chicken in honey mustard mixture, then coat with crumbs.
In a non-stick skillet, (medium heat), cook chicken in butter until juices run clear.

title: granny smith stir-fry
directions: Cut pork into 1/2-inch strips.
Core and slice apples.
Chop green onions.
Stir-fry pork until done; add apples, pepper and onions.
Continue to stir-fry until tender-crisp.
Add pecans.
Mix together the broth, brown sugar, vinegar, cornstarch, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Add the sauce to the skillet and cook over medium heat.
Stir until sauce thickens.

title: aunt helen's sauerbraten
directions: Marinate meat in vinegar, water, pickle spices and onion for 2 days, turning meat frequently.
Drain meat.
Brown all sides. Strain vinegar water.
Simmer meat in strained vinegar water until almost done.
Remove meat; carve in thin slices.
Mix ketchup, mustard, brown sugar and gingersnaps with vinegar water and flour to make gravy.
Put meat back in gravy.
Heat and serve over noodles or whatever.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: delicious chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in a bowl.
In a boiler bring the oleo, cocoa, water and Crisco to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute and pour into dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, vinegar, eggs, soda, vanilla and mix.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 11 x 16 pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: chocolate caramel apples
directions: You will need 12 wooden skewers.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix together the hamburger, sausage, green pepper, onion, egg, rice, salt and pepper; roll into balls.
Boil cabbage until wilted; take leaves off.
Wrap meat mixture and roll in leaves. In large pot, put a layer of kraut in bottom, then a layer of cabbage rolls, then layer of kraut, then rolls and so on, until all are gone.
Pour tomato sauce on top of cabbage rolls.
Put water in pot until liquid comes to the top of the rolls.
Boil slowly for about 1 1/2 hours, or until done.

title: salmon rice salad
directions: Put salmon, rice, egg, lemon juice, mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper in bowl. Toss thoroughly with a fork.
Gently mix in peas.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serve with tomato soup and muffins.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put potatoes in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt 1 stick margarine with onions.
Pour over potatoes.
In bowl, mix together soups, sour cream, cheese and bacon bits.
Pour over potatoes.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Remove from heat and stir in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: venison pepper steak
directions: Cut venison in 1-inch strips; marinate in soy sauce; season with salt and pepper.
In frying pan or wok put oil, peppers and onions; brown venison strips too.
After browned, simmer to tenderness, 15 to 30 minutes.
Add water.
Do not overcook venison.
Add whole tomatoes; simmer until hot.
Add 1/4 cup flour to water and thicken; if not enough, add a little more flour and water.
Add this to mixture in pan.
Heat through.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: the sun ball
directions: Beat cream cheese with mustard, garlic powder and wine until smooth.
Beat
in olives and Cheddar cheese.
Form into ball. Wrap in wax paper.
Chill, then roll in sunflower seeds.
Garnish with additional whole pitted ripe olives.

title: crock-pot soup
directions: Brown stew meat and onion.
Combine all ingredients in large crock-pot.
Heat on low for 7 to 8 hours or 4 hours on high.

title: strawberry dream pie
directions: Cook first five ingredients over medium heat until boiling and thick.
Chill and add Dream Whip.
Add sliced strawberries.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.

title: amaretto chocolate cheesecake(need spring-form pan)
directions: Mix and press into spring-form pan.
Chill.

title: baked tomatoes with topping
directions: Cut tomatoes in half.
Put in a round baking casserole. Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
Saute onion in butter in skillet.
Add to croutons with other ingredients (may need a few drops liquid).
Spread on tomato halves.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Remove from oven and cover each tomato half with shredded cheese.
Put in oven until melted.

title: party snacks
directions: You will need toothpicks (plastic works best) and a foil covered styrofoam cone.
